title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water, then add sugar and shortening.
Add salt and flour.
Knead until smooth, then put back in bowl and grease the top.
Let rise until double, then knead on bread board.
Put into loaf pans; grease the top.
Let rise to fill the pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until loaves sound hollow when knocked.

title: cream puffs in a pan
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Add flour.
Beat until dough leaves the side of pan.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Beat cream cheese and milk.
Add pudding and beat well. Spread over top of crust.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Sprinkle cream of tartar over mixture, mixing well.
Fold in crushed saltines, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into ungreased (see note) 9-inch square pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from stove and let cool completely.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 1/2 cups juice.
Heat and stir until jello is dissolved.
Add Coke.
Have a deep bowl as it foams up. Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Whisk softened cream cheese into partially set jello mixture.
Add fruit and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
When set, cover with Cool Whip and a few chopped pecans.

title: fish boats
directions: Thaw fish fillets, if frozen.
Melt margarine.
Mix with A.1. sauce and lemon juice.
Cut fish into serving pieces.
Place each serving in center of a piece of Reynolds Wrap.
Cup foil and pour sauce over fish.
Loosely seal edges of each "fish boat."
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Unwrap fish boats, sprinkle with paprika and serve in foil.
(Place boats on cookie sheet.)

title: reuben dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low heat until Swiss cheese is melted. Serve with party/cocktail rye bread.

title: cauliflower pie
directions: Boil cauliflower 10 minutes and drain.
Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Spread with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Put eggs, Bisquick, salt, pepper and milk in blender; process.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Mix soup, milk and pepper.
Blend together until vegetables are coated.
Put layer of coated vegetables into casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of cheese on top, then put in rest of vegetable mixture and finish with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach, potato soup and milk until mixed well.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Add chicken broth and warm through. Add sour cream just before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place milk and sugar in large saucepan.
Stir constantly and bring to a full boil.
Boil exactly 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Stir until all is melted and fudge has a glazed appearance.
Add nuts, if desired. Put into buttered pan and refrigerate 6 hours before cutting. Makes 5 pounds.
May be frozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut on bottom of greased/floured 9 x 13 pan. Mix the cake mix according to directions and pour over pecans and coconut. (Can use other cake mix.) Mix the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Spoon over cake and bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes. Let cool completely before cutting.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker meal.
Form into patties then coat with cracker meal. Fry in hot oil after refrigerating for 1hour.
Drain on paper towels.

title: apple relish
directions: Boil all ingredients for 1/2 hour.
Cool and serve with meat dishes.
Especially good with pork.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion (drain). Add tomatoes, soup, rice, salt, oregano and thyme. Simmer for 5 minutes. Put in baking dish. Top with cheese. Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: tropical salad
directions: Combine juices and water, bring to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in liquid.
Chill until syrupy.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas and coconut into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: line's fried chicken
directions: Add beaten egg to milk.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Dip in milk and egg mixture.
Batter chicken in flour.
Deep-fry or cook in electric skillet.
Keep chicken covered with lid until done on one side.
Turn chicken over and put lid back on until chicken is done.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then add egg and stir.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix all these things together.
Seed cherries and add.
Add next cup of sugar and mix and pour over top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry until golden brown.
Mix tomato juice, butter, hot sauce and vinegar in saucepan and heat.
Coat chicken in mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Ranch dressing and sliced carrot sticks.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Mix all together in a double boiler until tidbits are melted. Spoon out on waxed paper in small lumps.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat all ingredients except eggs.
Then pour over boiled and peeled eggs and seal.
Makes 1 quart.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add milk until thoroughly mixed.
Add confectioners sugar until you reach the correct consistency.

title: beverly slimm's tangy chicken and vegetable baked casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, butter, lemon juice, mustard and pepper.
In 2-quart casserole, combine vegetables and chicken.
Stir in mayonnaise mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Broil 8 to 10-inches from heat source, until bread crumbs are lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Using an electric mixer, cream the peanut butter and butter until very soft and smooth.
Beat in powdered sugar until smooth, then beat in half of the graham cracker crumbs.
Beat until well blended and moist.
Mix in remaining crumbs with hands.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, patting evenly.
Melt chocolate and pour over cracker mixture.
While chocolate is still soft, mark off desired size squares or bars and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugars. Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter and mix well. Add soda and oats and mix well. Add chocolate chips and M&M's. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 200 cookies.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape lightly with your fingers into 1-inch balls. Brown on all sides in a lightly greased skillet.
Put into a deep pan 2 cups consomme or stock or 1 can consomme and 1/2 can concentrated tomato soup.
Heat and add meat balls.
Cover and cook over very low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Add extra consomme or water from time to time if necessary to keep the meat balls from sticking.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Dip fish in batter immediately before frying.

title: limas and bacon
directions: Brown bacon lightly.
Add onion.
Cook over low heat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over lima beans.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour into greased baking dish. Spread fruit on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix soup and milk together.
Layer broccoli alternately with soup mixture and cheese in casserole dish.
Mix melted butter with the crushed crackers. Put on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Drop teaspoonfuls into sugar and form into balls coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Cookies will flatten and crinkle.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat the egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and salt until very light.
Combine the egg mixtures; stir until thoroughly blended.
Add the whipped cream, milk and brandy; beat well.
Add the rum.
Pour into a gallon jug; store in a cool place.
Shake or stir thoroughly before serving.
Serve in small cups; sprinkle with nutmeg. Serves 30.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Note: Read instructions carefully before proceeding.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix flour and soda together and set aside.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer blend sugars and butter at medium speed, scraping down sides of bowl.
Add egg, vanilla and banana; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add flour mixture, chocolate chips, oats and walnuts and blend at low speed until just combined.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake 20 to 24 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Transfer immediately to a cool surface. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and yeast. Mix well.
Refrigerate if desired.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll dough to 1 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased 7 X 7 inch pan.
Let rise slightly. Bake at 400 degrees until brown, about 12 - 15 minutes.
Yield 1 dozen.

title: pasta salad supreme
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and rinse under cool water.
Chop onion, pepper and cucumber; add to noodles. Pour salad dressing over noodles.
Add 1/2 of the bottle of Salad Supreme; save the rest for another time.
Toss and chill.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook egg yolk, sugar, salt, vinegar, pineapple, syrup and butter in double boiler until thick; cool.
Fold in whipped cream, white cherries, marshmallows, pineapple and oranges.
May add maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, mix with Rice Krispies.
Stir until coated.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: southwest salad(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Put cooked macaroni in large salad bowl; pour vinegar over macaroni and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Add oil, celery, green pepper, onions, Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce, chilies, salt, pepper, beans, corn, olives and mayonnaise to macaroni mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.
Taste for seasonings before serving.
(There should be a suggestion of the chilies and the tart tang of vinegar, but only a minimal amount of mayonnaise.)

title: clam loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and pack into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add oregano, tomato paste, soup, water, vinegar and garlic salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon roll
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and 1 tsp salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening until fine crumbs are formed.
Add milk and stir with a fork to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, knead gently for 8-10 times.
Roll into a 10 x
12 inch rectangle.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Soften braunschweiger to room temperature.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add the Cool Whip. Fold in strawberries and juice.
Drain the pineapple; dice the bananas.
Chop the pecans and fold all of these into the mixture also.
Freeze in an 6 x 11-inch loaf pan lined with Saran Wrap. Slice just before serving.

title: taco burgers
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 12-inch oblong burgers.
Grill or broil until done.
Serve if desired taco shells with lettuce and Cheddar cheese or on a bun.

title: praline pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and liqueur, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake test done.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.

title: baked parmesan chicken legs
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, oregano, pepper and salt; set aside. Lightly saute garlic in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in remaining butter.
Dip each piece of chicken in butter and then in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in long, shallow pan.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs and butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: christmas morning coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut the rolls in half and put in pan. Sprinkle the dry pudding mix on them.
Mix the 1 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Melt the margarine and mix with the brown sugar. Pour over rolls.
Cover and let rise 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep south pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add oil, two tablespoons at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt. Alternate milk and flour, ending with flour.
Bake in greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool on cake rack.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut raw rhubarb into bite size pieces.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar, pinch of salt, 2 rounds tbsp. flour and 1 egg.
Stir together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put 4 dots of margarine on top of mixture before putting top crust on pie.
Bake 425 for 20 minutes or 375 for 30 minutes.
Check on pie as it can become done in a shorter time.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Place into the freezer, stirring often.
Makes 1 qt.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add sugar, oil and egg mixture, then oats and cornflakes.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes or to desired brownness. If making smaller cookies, bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield:
6 dozen or more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together
and
sprinkle
cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, onion, pepper and pimento.
Place over low heat; add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Mix together macaroni, cheese sauce and tuna.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: tutu's peach pie
directions: Place peaches in unbaked pie crust. Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over peaches; sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking, flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: holiday apple cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, mix apples, sugar, oil, cranraisins and nuts.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring cream cheese to room
temperature. Beat cheese until creamy, add pineapple juice a little at a time. Fold in Cool Whip. Add rest of ingredients. Let set in refrigerator over night before serving.

title: baked stew
directions: Combine all ingredients with stew meat.
Stir together lightly.
Bake, covered, in 325° oven for 3 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's ole fashioned bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add vanilla flavoring and cinnamon and mix.
Next, add milk and stir well.
Tear bread slices into small pieces and add.
Let stand and soak bread for 10 minutes.
Last, add raisins.
Pour in greased pan and cook for 45 to 55 minutes in preheated oven at 425°.

title: christine's cushaw pie
directions: Peel cushaw.
Cut in pieces and cook until done.
Mash to get all lumps out.
Beat egg yolks until foamy; add to cushaw with sugar, milk and spices.
Keep egg whites for top.
Cook mixture on top of stove, stirring to keep eggs mixed until thickened.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake according to package directions. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add a little sugar and vanilla. Spread over pie and brown.

title: green bean and pepper salad
directions: In bowl, mix beans, green pepper, cukes and onions.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: company roast beef
directions: The day before, place meat in a Dutch oven.
Combine everything else and pour over roast.
Bake at 325° for at least 4 hours or until very tender.
Cool until room temperature.
Put dish in refrigerator and leave overnight.
The next day, slice meat, put back in sauce and reheat.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Pour 3 teaspoons of oil into heavy skillet.
When hot, add chicken, fry until brown, turn to other side to brown.
When chicken is brown on both sides, drain off oil.
Then put chicken back in pan. Pour barbecue over chicken, turn heat to simmer, cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes until chicken is tender and done on the inside.
Serve with a salad and vegetable of your choice.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients; stir in the Mazola and milk.
Drop the mixture by small tablespoonfuls two inches apart on an oiled biscuit pan.
Bake in a quick oven (375° t o 400°) for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in greased skillet at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Scramble-fry sausage in skillet until done, but not brown. Drain excess grease.
Add sausage to Bisquick and cheese.
Mix thoroughly until well blended.
Roll into balls about the size of a marble.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 10 minutes.

title: meatball mushroom sandwiches
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef, sausage, bread crumbs, egg and oregano.
Mix lightly, but well.
Shape into 16 (1 1/4-inch) meatballs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook meatballs 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes until meatballs are thoroughly cooked, stirring occasionally.
Spoon 4 meatballs and about 1/4 cup of the sauce onto each roll.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple dessert dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Pour in can of pineapple and spread to corners.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over and smooth out.
Melt butter/margarine and pour over mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake mix browns lightly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli.
Mix sour cream or mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion, then spread water chestnuts, crumbled bacon and almonds over broccoli, then spoon the soup mixture over that.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar with cinnamon in a bowl and mix well.
Separate biscuits. Dip biscuits in butter and roll in cinnamon mixture until coated. Overlap biscuits around edge of greased 9-inch cake pan. Overlap remaining biscuits in center.
Drizzle remaining butter over top and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: sour cream cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together except butter and corn flakes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes; pour butter over top (enough to cover) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with apples.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Fill with apple mixture. Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes, reduce temperature to moderate 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. (I use a large bowl.)
Combine bananas, sugar, eggs and butter and beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in 2 cups of nuts and Nestle butterscotch chips. Pour batter equally into two well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Sprinkle tops equally with remaining 2/3 cup pecans. Bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix.
Use 2 teaspoons or more to cup of hot water.

title: apple taffy dip
directions: Blend together and dip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add rice to salt in boiling water.
Cover and cook for 7 to 10 minutes, until water is absorbed.
Add milk and margarine.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to very low when milk has ceased boiling; cook until milk is almost absorbed.
(Add sugar, raisins, vanilla and eggs together.)
Pour into rice; stir slowly until rice begins to thicken.
May serve hot, warm or cold.

title: lo-cal dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: blueberry yogurt pudding
directions: In a bowl fold together Cool Whip, yogurt, pie filling and fresh blueberries. Spoon into sherbet glasses. Chill. Garnish as desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and batter.
Add stuffing mix.
Place in casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend well.
Top with 1/3 cup blanched almonds, sauteed.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fish pie
directions: Take 1 tablespoon butter off and put in skillet.
Add onions and saute until lightly brown.
Stir in fish; mix gently.
Melt another 1/2 tablespoon butter in a 1-quart baking dish.
Lay in slices of egg and tomato; top with fish.
Keep doing over until all ingredients are used.
Mix 3/4 of the egg with mashed potatoes, almonds and parsley.
Spread over top of baking dish. Dot with remaining butter and brush with remaining egg.
Cook for 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: tuna-hominy casserole
directions: Mix hominy, tomato sauce, tuna, green pepper, onion and cumin in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.

title: nippy cheddar cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together cheeses until smooth, about 2 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to cheeses and beat until thoroughly combined.
Spoon on plastic wrap; cover and shape into a ball.
Chill for 1 hour; remove from refrigerator and roll cheese ball in pecans.
Rewrap and chill another 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 1 cheese ball.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: scallops with garlic
directions: Melt butter and garlic on low heat.
Add garlic powder; mix. Place scallops in square 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour butter mixture over scallops; toss lightly.
Sprinkle parsley over. Broil for under 10 minutes.
Great served with rice or thin spaghetti.
Use same ingredients for sauce!
Serves 2 to 3.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Add rice and chicken to dressing.
Mix in water chestnuts.
Chill thoroughly.
Add grapes and cashews just before serving.
Very good.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with 3 tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cream cheese.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar; cream well after each addition.
Blend in egg, flour and vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs until thick and light in color.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating until thickened.
Add baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in chocolate mixture, nuts, 1 teaspoon vanilla and almond extract.
Spread cream cheese mixture over top; spoon on remaining chocolate batter.
Zigzag through batter with spatula or knife to marble.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool, then cut.
Makes 16 to 20.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate about 4 hours before serving.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and place in buttered casserole dish.
Cook and chop chicken and place on broccoli.
Cover with layer of sauce.

title: lemon scones
directions: Toss peel in 2 tablespoons flour and set aside.
Sift flour with salt, sugar, soda and baking powder. Cut in the butter until crumbly. Add peel, egg, yogurt and orange peel.
Blend well. Divide into 30 balls.
Flatten to 1/2-inch thick. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool and serve with butter and jam.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients and drain.
Place in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Serve with tortilla chips.
This makes a full crock-pot.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour into pan, but do not stir.
Add any fruit you desire (we prefer blackberries) and as much as you want.
Be sure to use enough to cover the mixture good. Sprinkle one cup of sugar all over the top.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Easy!

title: quick fudge sundaes
directions: Mix chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Heat slowly; stir to blend.
Beat in marshmallow cream until blended.
Serve warm or cool over ice cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix for filling.
Combine remaining dry cake mix, margarine and 1 egg in large bowl; mix well until crumbly.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.
Combine reserved cake mix, corn syrup, sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla; beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes, until filling is set.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 3 dozen.
Serve warm, if possible.
Add 1 dab of Cool Whip.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cornstarch and turmeric and mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Return to stove and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Use as a basting sauce or a dip.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet (in water makes it softer).
Drain. Return to pan and add seasoning mix and tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 to 1 can water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add broken chips, stirring to mix well.
Lower heat and simmer another 5 minutes.
Place in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and cover with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Low-salt Version:
Omit garlic salt; add instead 2 teaspoons garlic powder.

title: menehune pineapple bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, flour and pineapple.
Mix in bread.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of casserole dish. Mix soup and milk together. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle generously with cheese. Top with dry stuffing mix and drizzle with margarine. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: dandelions and fritters
directions: Mix the fritters (first 5 ingredients) and fry in Crisco or bacon grease.
Dig dandelions and go through 8 waters.
Wilt them in a frying pan with a little grease, hot water, vinegar and salt. Put them on the fritters.
They make a delightful dish.

title: instant cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into well-greased baking dish. Spoon pie filling onto mix.
Then pour melted butter over top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and melted butter.
Press on bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
(Cool well.)

title: chalupas ole
directions: Heat beans and spread on chips.
Top with selection of toppings.

title: chocolate chip coffeecake
directions: Scald milk; stir in margarine and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; sprinkle yeast into very warm water in large bowl of mixer; stir to dissolve.
Add milk mixture, eggs and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed until smooth (15 seconds).
With spoon, blend in 1 cup flour and morsels.
Turn into well-greased 10-inch angel cake pan.
Sprinkle with topping (recipe follows), cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 35 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Let cool on wire rack.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan and let set 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer until set.

title: individual beef wellingtons
directions: Trim fat from steaks.
Panbroil 1 1/2 minutes each side. Drain.
Place on rack in broiler pan coated with spray.
Drizzle 1/4 teaspoon Worcestershire over each.
Spread pate on top of each steak.
Lightly coat each phyllo sheet with cooking spray.
Fold in half.
Spray.
Fold again to form 6 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch rectangle. Snip strip from end.
Set aside.
Drape rectangle over each steak. Tuck under; crumple strip into a ball.
Place on top.
Spray.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or to desired doneness.
Combine consomme, wine and cornstarch.
Stir well.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve with steaks.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine
ingredients in mixer
except
for
the
crust. Beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour
into unbaked graham cracker crust. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at
Chill
and serve with your favorite topping.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with broken taco chips. Brown ground beef with onion.
Spread on top of taco chips.
Then spread tomato soup, next, mushroom soup and next, chili over mixture.
Sprinkle chopped olives over this and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine water and apple juice in saucepan.
Add Kool-Aid mix and spices.
Mix well and bring just to a boil.
Serve hot. Garnish with cinnamon sticks.
Serves 16.

title: graham snacks
directions: Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place graham cracker quarters on foil.
Pour mixture over graham crackers, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 9 minutes.
Separate and place on cooling rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Beat.
Add Cool Whip and Mix.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread pudding mixture over crackers and top with another layer of crackers.
Spread frosting over crackers, carefully.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Stir together cottage cheese and eggs.
Fold in sausage, Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, ham, pepper, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Turn into partially baked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 8.

title: hot cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples and cranberries.
Sprinkle on lemon juice. Cover with sugar and place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix oatmeal, nuts, brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over fruit in casserole dish.
Bake uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla well. Alternate flour and milk, mixing well after each.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour mixture into it.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high for 4 hours or
low for 8 hours. Serve over rice.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together like cake mix texture.
(If not, keep adding ingredients.)
Put in cake pans.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: bing cherry jello
directions: Drain juice from fruit; heat to make jello.
Add enough Coca-Cola to make 4 cups liquid.
When mixture begins to jell, add fruit and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, crumbled, into mixture.
Jell completely.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature and cream with the sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside to cool.

title: coleslaw
directions: Chop slaw mix finely. Mix in salt and pepper. Add sugar and mayonnaise and mix well.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix and pack into 4-cup mold.
Chill at least three hours. Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour warm water
in
large
mixing
bowl.
Add yeast and sugar.
Beat
with
mixer
dough blenders until dissolved.
Let set while
mixing
and
measuring other ingredients.
Run dough blenders and add part
of flour, salt, eggs and oil, then blend in remaining flour.
Let rise until it doubles its size.
Then make into rolls or refrigerate.

title: mema's cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a frying pan.
Pour mixture into melted butter.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Break pretzels up and take off salt.
Put in a 9 x 15-inch glass dish.
Drizzle oil on pretzels.
Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over pretzels.
Do not mix.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix and microwave 2 to 3 additional minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done; crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage and sprinkle in pie shell.
Add remaining ingredients into beaten eggs and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: tomato, cucumber, onion and basil flower salad
directions: Toss tomatoes, cucumber, onion and cheese together.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and water.
Drizzle vinaigrette over veggies and cheese.
Toss gently with basil flowerets.
Serve room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf with stuffing(buddy's favorite meat loaf recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ground beef, crumbs and onions lightly into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and parsley; mix lightly.
Divide into 3 parts; put 1 part into a 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with 6 ounces cheese.
Spread with second part of ground beef mixture.
Cover with 6 ounces cheese. Spread with remaining ground beef mixture.
Invert loaf onto jelly roll pan or foil-covered cookie sheet, turning up edges of foil to form rim.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with rest of cheese. Bake for 5 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Slice.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Cook sugar, baking soda and buttermilk to the soft-ball stage, stirring constantly while cooking.
Remove from fire and add butter, pecans halves and vanilla.
Beat until stiff enough to hold shape when dropped from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, vanilla, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix 2 small packages chocolate pie filling with 3 cups milk.
Cook until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool and pour over other mixture.

title: berry gazpacho
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Simmer for about 15 minutes. Cover and chill. Pour wine mixture through a wire mesh strainer into a large bowl, discarding bean and mint. Process strawberries and 1 cup water in a blender until smooth; pour through wire mesh strainer into wine mixture, discarding
seeds. Stir in honey and berries and chill. Serve with a melon ball size scoop of raspberry sorbet, and garnish with mint leaves. Makes about 8 one-cup serving.

title: garden slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar. Put in Pyrex dish. Bake at 250° for 10 minutes. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 3/4 cup sugar. Spread over cooled pretzel layer. Be sure to seal edges. Mix jello with boiling water and strawberries. Pour over cheese mixture layer. Chill overnight.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: *Nuts are pecans, English walnuts or black walnuts.

title: b b q chicken
directions: 1. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
2. Rub oil on skin, put salt and pepper or season salt in
cavity & outside skin. Stuff cavity with onion and
garlic.
3. Cook on grill 45-60 minutes at 350° until juice is
clear, not red at thigh.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly.
Spoon in 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and then chips on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix milk, 1 can crushed pineapple with juice, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Combine the ingredients and mix.
Drain second can of pineapple and add to mixture.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake for 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first five ingredients. Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 10 oblong patties. Brown on both sides. Drain.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Cook slowly until done.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl.
Heat milk and butter until butter is melted.
Add to first ingredients with eggs. Add remaining flour.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead until no longer sticky.
Set aside to rise.
Punch down.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll out large circle. Cut into triangles.
Lightly spread melted butter on dough. Roll up large end first.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple-raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in pineapple.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and beat well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: wheat germ muffins
directions: Mix Bisquick, wheat germ and sugar in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine egg, water, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat mixture smooth with mixer.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients; stir until moistened (don't over mix).
Spoon into muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: popovers
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes or until consistency resembles heavy cream.
Divide batter between 6 buttered cups or popover molds.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: cool summer pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and syrup until thick and clear. Add desired flavor of Jell-O.
Take whatever fruit you want (fresh, canned or frozen) and put in pie pan; pour Jell-O mixture over.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole ii
directions: Cook potatoes and add cream cheese; mash. Add sour cream; mash. Add garlic, salt and pepper. Fold in chives or dill. Place in buttered 2 quart casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered spoons
directions: Heat in 1 cup glass measuring cup at 50% power for 1/2 minute. Stir until nice and smooth.
Dip plastic spoon in chocolate.
Place on cutting board with wax paper.
Melt white bark in microwave and go back and forth over spoons to drizzle.
Wrap in clear or colored plastic wrap.
Use to stir coffee.
Make a basket arrangement for hostess gift.

title: cream cheese thumbprint
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Roll in slightly beaten egg whites, then in finely chopped nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press thumb into dough to make slight indentation.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, fill dent with frosting, cherries or jelly.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° to 450° until brown.

title: s'more bars
directions: Blend together all ingredients until crumbly.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips and 2 cups miniature marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon shortening.
Drizzle over marshmallows after baking.

title: sweetened instant condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (about the same as a can of commercial type milk).
This is thinner.
You can add less water or cook a short time on top of range to thicken as needed.

title: scones(english specialty)
directions: In bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter. Combine with your fingers or wooden spoon until coarse crumbs form.
Add buttermilk, quickly stir to form a dough.
Divide dough in half.
Form each half into a ball.
Flatten to a round.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cut each crosswise into 4 pieces but not all the way through.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Good served with orange marmalade or jam. Yields 8, 175 calories per serving.

title: crabmeat lasagna
directions: Combine shrimp soup and crabmeat.
Combine in separate bowl: cottage cheese, cream cheese, egg, basil, lemon juice and chopped onion.

title: spicy pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 20 to 24 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring mixture to a sudden boil, then simmer.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
The last 15 minutes of cooking time, add cleaned shrimp.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Can be served chilled over green salad.

title: pear salad
directions: Arrange pears on platter. Spoon mayonnaise onto each pear. Sprinkle cheese and top each with a cherry.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients and 8 ounces cheese.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add stuffing and mix well.
Pack into casserole dish with squash mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chicken sauterne
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: 90 minute rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour, salt and dry yeast.
Heat milk, oleo and water to 120° (until oleo melts).
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour and beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in only enough more flour to handle (the secret is to keep the dough as soft as possible to handle).
On flour board, knead about 2 to 3 minutes.
Make into rolls (about 12 pieces).
Place in greased 8-inch pan.
Pour 1-inch depth boiling water into large pan.
Place on bottom rack of stove. Set rolls on rack above water and cover.
Let rise for 30 minutes in closed oven.
Turn oven on to 375°.
Remove pan of water and uncover rolls.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper; brown slowly in butter.
Place chicken in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add soup to drippings.
Slowly add sherry and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover; cook 25 additional minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and butter until done.
Mix squash with soda crackers, soup, eggs and 1/2 cup cheese and pour in buttered dish. Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: boursin cheese spread
directions: Soften cheese and butter.
Mix all together.
Can be frozen in containers.
If it separates on thawing, stir in a little cream.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat together the soup and gelatine until hot.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cool to set.
Serves 10 to 15 as an appetizer.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crispy Doritos or tortilla chips warmed in the oven or microwave.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine the beef, mushroom soup, mushrooms, soup mix and wine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours. Serve over egg noodles.

title: pasta primavera(lori)
directions: Heat wok or large, deep skillet over medium-high heat.
Add butter, onion and garlic and saute until onion is softened.
Mix in mushrooms, cauliflower, broccoli and carrot.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Increase heat to high.
Add cream, chicken broth and basil.
Allow mixture to boil until liquid is slightly reduced, about 3 minutes.
Stir in peas, ham and green onion.
Cook 1 minute more.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add drained pasta and cheese, tossing until thoroughly combined and pasta is heated.
Place onto large serving platter.
Serve immediately.

title: indecent pie
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish to form a crust.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar together until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake in a 325° preheated oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Roll out rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch mix. Spread on baked crust.
Chop vegetables very fine.
Sprinkle over cream cheese.
Spread and press down so vegetables are secured in cream cheese mixture.

title: chilies with beef
directions: Season beef to taste.
Brown beef in saucepan.
Add seasoning packet.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Cook until noodles are done.
Serve.

title: pay day candy bars
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and butter for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and corn flakes.
Spread on cookie sheet and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: spider bread
directions: Mix egg and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and 1 Tbsp. melted shortening.
Get skillet hot on top of stove, melt about a Tbsp. of shortening in the skillet and then add the corn bread mixture.
Let cook on burner for about one minute and then place in a 375° oven for 20-25 minutes.
Spider Bread gets it's name from the iron skillets with legs that were used to bake this tasty corn bread in the "old days".
I use a 12 inch iron skillet and double the recipe. It makes a very moist corn bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit. Combine orange juice, sugar and flavorings. Pour over fruit mixture, tossing lightly. Cover and chill 2 - 3 hours.

title: heavenly coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, coconut, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks and Pet milk.
Cook over medium fire, stirring constantly.
When thickened, add oleo and vanilla.
Put in baked crust.

title: broccoli salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients for dressing and chill.

title: mrs. "j's" original coconut candy
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips in double boiler. Remove from burner.
Add chopped nuts and coconut and mix well. (Mixture will feel crumbly.)
Drop by hand in desired sizes of foil-lined pans.
Place in freezer 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and put in tin or on plate and cover.
Store in refrigerator until well set.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush or grind cookies and set aside.
Blend in a mixer the rest of the ingredients.
Layer cookies and pudding mix in 6 or 7-inch flowerpot (new).
Keep enough crumbs to sprinkle on the top for added decoration.
Arrange artificial flower stems in the middle of the "dirt dessert".

title: venison steak and gravy(vernie's specialty)
directions: Use however much venison you like.
Slice into strips and beat.
Soak in milk.
Fry using flour and seasonings as usual. Add cream of chicken with gravy mixture.
Put steak back into gravy.
Add a touch of Kitchen Bouquet and onion.
Great taste.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
While the spaghetti is cooking, cut tomato and cucumber into small pieces.
Use 1/4 bottle of salad supreme and 1 small bottle of dressing.
Combine all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Mix well and serve.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add milk and butter.
Microwave
on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on High for another 2 1/2 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Add vanilla and beat with a spoon just a little bit.

title: honey spice snaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Blend in egg and honey.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Dip half of each ball into water and then into granulated sugar.
Place the sugared side up on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: help your heart baked pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir in the pumpkin and add vanilla, evaporated milk, orange rind and egg whites.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in brandy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 more minutes or until done.

title: microwave dried herbs
directions: Wash herbs in cold water and dry in salad spinner or paper towels.
Pull leaves from stems.
Place herb leaves between 2 paper towels in microwave.
Bake on High power for 4 minutes.
Replace towels if damp.
Continue to microwave in 1 or 2 minute increments until herbs are crisp to the touch.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add mayonnaise, water and vanilla. Mix well; grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut mochi cake
directions: Mix everything together;
pour	into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunshine fizz
directions: Pour orange juice, pineapple juice and club soda into a large bowl.
Add sherbet and mix with a beater or whip.
Makes 2 tall glasses.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press into mini muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately press 1 peanut butter cup into each hot crust center.
Allow to cool.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in sealed container.
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons in 1 cup hot water or to taste.

title: microwave southwestern-style pork chops
directions: Dip both sides of pork chops in taco sauce and then in crushed tortilla chips, coating well.
Place pork chops in 12 x 8 x 2-inch (2-quart) glass baking dish, with meaty sides to outside of dish. Cover with waxed paper.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Add garlic salt to Cheddar cheese, pimento and eggs.
Add mayonnaise to blend.
Mix thoroughly.

title: dreamy apricot mold
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add gelatin and stir until completely dissolved.
Add fruit (pineapple and baby food) and set aside to cool. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add condensed milk and lemon juice; continue beating until smooth. Stir in gelatin mixture, then nuts. Pour into 9-cup mold and chill until firm.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix shredded squash, green peppers, onions and pimientos in a large container.
Pour 1/4 cup salt over the vegetables and let stand overnight.
Next day, rinse and drain vegetables.
Add vinegar, sugar and all spices.
Cook 30 minutes by bringing to a slow boil, then reducing heat until it just stops boiling.
Put in clean, hot jars and can.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients (may need more milk to make batter thin enough to pour in pan).
For best results, spray 9-inch iron skillet with cooking spray (like Pam).
Bake at 425° until edges of bread are showing brown.
Turn on broil and brown top.

title: tuna noodle supreme casserole
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Stir together in large bowl, sour cream, Miracle Whip, cheese, milk and mustard; salt and pepper to taste. Add hot pasta, tuna, broccoli, pepper and onion. Stir until evenly blended. Place mixture in 2-quart baking dish; cover. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.

title: eggs maria luisa(huevos maria luisa)
directions: Mix cream with salt and pepper in an ovensafe dish.
On top of the mix, put the eggs and cover with cheese and small pieces of butter.
Put in oven until egg white solidifies and yolk is soft.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt in a double boiler; stir in milk, cook stirring until thickened.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks and combine with 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to mixture and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Layer dish with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat and top with meringue.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place breasts in long pan; cover with well drained sauerkraut. Cover next with cheese slices; spread dressing over cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serves 8.

title: savory cheese potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes.
Put boiling water and salt in saucepan; add potatoes, cover and boil 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and save 3/4 cup drained water.

title: fruit applesauce cake
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients, but applesauce and soda, to heat in saucepan. Stir warm into fruit mixture.
Pour into loaf pans. Decorate with cherries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool in pan.

title: roasted eggplant and feta cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place eggplant cubes in a shallow baking pan; toss with 3/4 cup olive oil. Salt to taste.
Bake until cubes are soft, but not mushy, about 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Whisk together the remaining 3/4 cup olive oil, lemon juice, onion, garlic and oregano in a small bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Toss about half of the dressing with eggplant.
Arrange on a bed of spinach on a large platter. Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Drizzle with remaining dressing and garnish with fresh oregano sprigs.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Drain water from tuna fish.
Crush potato chips in bag.
Mix soup with milk.
Alternate layers of potato chips and tuna fish in a greased casserole, pouring part of the soup over each layer. Top with chips and remaining soup.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat until well mixed.
Cook 1 package of hot dogs.
Slice and add to sauce. Cook over low heat for 1/2 hour and serve.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and cornmeal.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/3 of the flour mixture and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat.
Repeat twice.
Pour in a greased 8-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: velveeta potatoes
directions: Slice peeled potatoes in thin slices.
In small saucepan or microwave combine cheese and milk until smooth.
Pour over potatoes in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange on bottom of greased baking dish.
Cook and bone chicken breasts; arrange in pieces over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Over cheese, spread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Can be fixed earlier and heated before serving.

title: mocha milk shake
directions: Dissolve instant coffee and instant milk in cold water.
Pour mixture into blender.
Spoon in chocolate ice cream.
Blend 25 seconds.
Pour into glasses.
Can top with whipped cream.

title: athenian chicken rolls
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook onions and celery 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in chicken, broth, parsley, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in cheese.
Cool completely.
Stir in eggs.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel sweet potatoes- slice- cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Pour water off.
Add butter, sugar, milk, allspice, eggs, and milk.
MIx with water.
Put in piecrust- bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Turn down to 300 degrees and bake for 15 minutes or until set.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (should be slightly browned around the edges). Serve with favorite crackers or chips. Great with Wheat Thins. May use "light" mayo and sour cream.

title: potato kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend all ingredients in blender. Pour into an 8-inch square greased dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Layer the following:
Soften cream cheese and spread over glass serving dish.
Sprinkle cheese over the cream cheese. Spread cocktail sauce over cheese.
Add bell pepper and tomatoes, enough to cover entire tray.
Add shrimp that were defrosted, they may be already cooked but may not be deveined.
Prepare the night before.
Serve with crackers.
Serves approximately 100.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Mix all together- refrigerate until firm. Roll in pecans. If you like, you can chop up jalapenos and mix that in too.

title: oatmeal wafers
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets and set aside.
In a medium-size bowl, mix the oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan or skillet, melt the margarine over moderate heat.
Add the margarine and maple syrup to the dry ingredients and mix well. Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto the baking sheets, spacing the cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove the cookies from the oven and let them harden on the baking sheets for 2 minutes before transferring to wire racks to cool.

title: cooked greens(spinach, escarole, chicory, endive or dandelions)
directions: Clean greens, removing roots and any wilted parts.
Wash several times in a large amount of water.
Boil greens in enough salted water to cover.
(Spinach is an exception; use just a small amount of water in cooking spinach.)
Cook until tender.
Remove from heat and drain thoroughly.
When cool, squeeze to remove all water.
Brown onions in oil, cooking slowly.
Add greens and seasoning to onions and toss lightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Lemon juice may be added for a tart flavor.

title: continental rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice and heat to boil.
Put rice in a casserole and add the heated mixture. Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: stromboli
directions: Note: For best results, have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Spray Pam into a 9-inch size pan or dish.
Combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, cooled margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well. Spoon batter over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and warm water. Stir well to dissolve sugar.
Pour water mixture over batter very slowly. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You may sprinkle a little sugar over top before baking, if desired.

title: elephant ears
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening; heat until shortening is melted.
Don't let mixture boil.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour, 2 cups at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Put in a greased bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Dust hands with flour.
Pinch off pieces of dough, about the size of a golfball.
Stretch each piece into a thin 6 to 8-inch circle.
Fry one at a time in oil (350°) until dough rises to the surface.
Turn and fry other side until light brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with sugar mixture.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil in a small saucepan over medium heat; cook, stirring often for 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Remove dressing from heat and cool for 30 minutes. Stir together chopped bell pepper and next 8 ingredients in a large bowl. Gently stir in dressing. Cover and chill salad for 8 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon. Keeps well in an airtight container in refrigerator for several days.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Oil or butter bread pans.
Thaw bread; do not let rise.
Roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Spread pepperoni over bread dough. Spread cheese over pepperoni; fold over bottom first, then top, then fold ends.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion and celery in margarine; set aside.
Mix soups and broth. Layer ingredients, starting with layer of noodles, then chicken, onion, celery, soup and nuts, ending with pimentos on top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly, about 1/2 hour. Makes a long casserole dish full.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Put strawberries in blender container; cover and blend on low speed until fruit is pureed.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Stir in lemonade concentrate until melted.
Add the cold water, cranberry juice and strawberry puree.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled ginger ale.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat oil in large iron skillet; set aside.
Mix in a large bowl: cornmeal, flour, eggs, creamed corn, grated cheese, hot peppers, onion and buttermilk to make the loose batter.
Add hot oil.
Sprinkle skillet with cornmeal.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake until brown on top.
Cool.
Loosen edge with knife.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with Hawaiian Cake Icing.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add sugar, dissolved cornstarch and egg.
Cook 1 minute, stirring until thickened.
Add vanilla. Cool.
Ladle over rice pudding.
Serves 8.

title: salmon southwest
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except salmon and green onions.
Microwave, uncovered, at High (full power) for 13 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Stir in salmon and green onions.
Cover; let stand 2 minutes.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Blend all ingredients together with mixer for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour batter into graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: ham-potato au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes 10 minutes; drain.
Layer potatoes, ham and drained mushrooms in shallow 2-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in flour, blending thoroughly.
Slowly add milk, stirring until thickened.
Fold in cheese and sour cream and pour over casserole.
Combine crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: stuffed breakfast bread
directions: Flatten dough into a rectangle shape to fit into loaf pan. Scramble eggs and set aside.
Cook sausage and set aside.
Put layer of eggs and layer of sausage on top of flattened dough. Sprinkle cheese over eggs and sausage.
Fold ends over mixture and then fold sides into center.
Coat loaf pan with cooking spray and put loaf into pan folded sides down.
Bake according to directions on bread package.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients and sift well.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots last and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let it cool before icing.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn.

title: white chili
directions: Put beans in heavy pot.
Cover with cold water by at least 3-inches and soak overnight.
Put chicken in large saucepan. Cover with water and cook until just tender, about 15 minutes. Drain, cool, remove skin and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Drain beans.
Heat oil in same pot to medium-high.

title: guacamole
directions: Cook asparagus and drain.
Dice tomatoes and chop green onions fine; add salt, green chilies, lemon juice and grated cheese.
Add all to asparagus and mash together with your hands.

title: jo's mile high strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a 9-inch pie pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: fresh strawberry chiffon cake
directions: Blend ingredients until fluffy and of good spreading consistency.
Add additional berries if icing appears too thick.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cream and melted butter, beating well. Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cover tops with pecan chips.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: freezer rhubarb jelly
directions: Put rhubarb, sugar and pineapple in bowl and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day boil for 20 minutes, then add jello (any kind) and pour in jars and freeze.

title: biscuits(make 'em - bake 'em in 10 minutes.)
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: chicken broccoli angel hair
directions: In 12-inch saute pan, combine olive oil and garlic and begin cooking so as to sweat the garlic (approximately 1 minute).
Add chicken, broccoli, chicken stock, salt, pepper and basil and bring to a boil (approximately 3 to 4 minutes).
Add butter and swirl into liquid mix to blend.
Poach pasta and add to mix.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given.
Mix well.
Spread butter in the pan.
Spread flour in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 38 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Heat any kind of fruit juice over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Crush graham crackers and add to marshmallow mixture. Add candied fruit, pecans and walnuts.
Mix well.
Line two loaf pans with wax paper.
Pour cake mix in pans and press down firmly.

title: chili dip
directions: Fry chicken livers with onion in butter until onions are tender and livers are cooked.
Chop liver and onions
very finely and add mayonnaise.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: party chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Wrap each piece with a slice of bacon. Cover bottom of baking dish with chipped beef.
Lay chicken on top. Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken. Refrigerate overnight. Cover and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: cream centers for dipped chocolates
directions: Mix all the confectioners sugar, butter, cream cheese and vanilla together.
This is a basic cream candy.
Add the peanut butter to make peanut creams or add the coconut to make coconut creams.
Shape into bite size pieces or shape into eggs; dip into chocolate.
Makes about 4 to 4 1/2 pounds.

title: easy-bake chicken
directions: Carefully measure the Italian salad dressing, lemon juice, instant bouillon granules and pepper.
Place them in a small bowl and stir gently to mix.
Arrange the chicken parts in a single layer in a large baking pan.
Spoon sauce mixture over each piece of chicken.
Set the oven temperature at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour. You can cook baked potatoes at the same time.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time and mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings last.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken 'n chips casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, taco sauce and chilies.
In an ungreased shallow 2-quart baking dish, layer half of the chicken, soup mixture, cheese and tortilla chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: english cooler
directions: Combine tea, rum, lemon juice and sugar in a tall glass.
Fill with ice.
Garnish with lemon. Makes 1 drink.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and milk
on low heat.
Add to sugar and salt and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: chocolate-pecan chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; stir into sugar mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chips in double boiler until smooth.
Stir in bourbon and Karo.
Let cool.
Combine crumbs, 10x sugar and nuts and add to melted chips.
Let sit 1/2 hour.
Shape into balls.
Roll in regular sugar.
Store airtight in cool place or in refrigerator.

title: lemon layered dessert
directions: Mix together.
Add remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: chocolate frosting(cooked)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in saucepan.
Cook at medium heat until mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter or margarine and flavoring. Stir and frost.

title: easy caramel frosting(this is another way to make caramel icing.)
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and milk; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool slightly, then beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.

title: italian beef
directions: Place meat, spices and water in roast pan; bake in a 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours, cutting string and basting the last 1/2 hour. Serve on Italian or French bread or hard rolls.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers (fine); chop cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Mix with vanilla wafers.
Add condensed milk.
Mix until moist.
Press in pan and put in icebox.

title: pumpkin nut waffles
directions: Sift together, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks, then combine with milk, shortening and pumpkin.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour onto hot waffle iron. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons pecans, then cook.
Makes 4 servings.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut wings into 3 sections at joints (I don't use the flipper end).
Costco sells 6 pound bag frozen party wings, already disjointed.
Soak chicken overnight in mixture of ingredients. Arrange pieces side by side in large flat baking sheet.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add apples. Put in the bottom of a pan.

title: granola cookies
directions: Mix together in a big bowl; make into small balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 48.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve and boil the first 2 ingredients and then let cool. Mix in the next 4 ingredients.
Freeze this mixture.
Let the mixture thaw a couple of hours before serving to allow it to get slushy, then add last 3 ingredients.
This makes 1 large punch bowl.

title: model-a wassail punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except orange and lemon slices. Bring to a boil.
Pour into a bowl and float lemon and orange slices.
Makes about 4 quarts (16 cups or 20 punch cup servings).

title: tanya's famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, blend oil, honey, eggs and extracts.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate for an hour before spooning by the teaspoonfuls onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: pineapple-apricot wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Strain and discard the spices.
Serve hot.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: egg custard
directions: You do not need a crust for this recipe.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry rice with 1/2 cup butter
for
1 minute.
Add 1 2/3 cups salted, boiling water to
this.
When
the
whole
thing starts to simmer vigorously, reduce heat to minimum; cover and cook until done (15 to 20 minutes).

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Peel
and cube potatoes and onions; cook, covered, in 2 cups water in large Dutch oven until almost done.
Add remainder
of water and remaining ingredients; simmer until potatoes are tender. Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all together well, using spoon, in large bowl. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Pour dry gelatin mix over fruit.
Stir to melt.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold into other mixture.
Refrigerate. Keeps several days.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix pastry ingredients.
Roll into long strips about 4 inches wide.
Spread filling on top.
Roll it like a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown or cooked.
Cool and slice.

title: lo-fat chicken
directions: Mix the orange zest, juice, onion and bouillon together and coat chicken.
Put in baking dish in single layer.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour juice and add water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water.
Add to the liquid.
Cook until thickened. Pour over chicken.
Put orange slice and grapes on chicken . Broil until fruit is heated through.

title: cheese sandwich
directions: Put butter in the bread.
Then put cheese in the bread.
Put it in a pan and cook.
Then eat it!

title: best ever fruitcake
directions: Mix all fruits, nuts and raisins in large bowl.
Add 1/4 cup dry ingredients from Bowl 2.

title: festive fruit cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and brown and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice, reserving remaining for frosting.
Stir until well blended. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to orange mixture, stirring until smooth. Add coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.
Blend confectioners sugar with butter and reserved orange concentrate.
Frost the hot cookies.

title: multi-bean soup
directions: This makes about eight 2-cup packages of beans.
Any dried peas or beans may be added to the mix.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, milk and Velveeta cheese until melted.
Add chilies, and green onion dip.
Mix. Set aside.
Brown meat and drain fat. Add salt and garlic; set off heat and combine Longhorn cheese and onions.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Put milk in freezer to cool.
Make up Jell-O with water, sugar, salt and juice and grated rind of lemons.
Put in refrigerator to set.
When nearly set, whip the milk stiff and add Jell-O.

title: lemon sweet chicken
directions: Skin and cut up chicken; coat with self-rising flour.
Pour small amount of Puritan oil into skillet and cook until brown. Drain all oil and place chicken back into skillet.
Combine lemon concentrate, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and water and pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes covered.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: velvet salad
directions: Seed and half the grapes (may substitute fruit cocktail).
Cut marshmallows and pineapple in small pieces.
Mix with cream.
Cook the yolk of 3 eggs with juice of 1 lemon until thick.
Cool and stir in fruit mixture, blending well.
Place in refrigerator until serving time.
This can be made the day before serving.

title: spaghetti slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook over low heat 4 to 5 hours.
One and one-half pounds of hamburger can be used in recipe.
Brown meat and drain before adding to mixture.
Sauce can be frozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: hula muffins
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 teaspoons juice for topping. Combine pineapple, eggs, milk and oleo.
Mix well.
Mix pancake mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to pineapple mix and stir until moistened.
Fill paper lined cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: easy brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar and syrup.
Cook until it starts to boil. Stir together soda, vanilla and water; set aside.
Cook sugar and syrup to 300° by candy thermometer.
While this is boiling, grease 2 jelly roll pans.
Put in oven to warm lightly.
Also put the peanuts in oven to warm.
When candy has reached 300°, remove from stove.
Add vanilla, soda and water.
Stir very fast.
Stir in nuts.
Take pans from oven and put on racks.
Spread candy on 2 pans.
When cold, break into eatable pieces.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix everything except potatoes, then pour over potatoes that have been thawed and put in a greased 11 x 13-inch pan. Put 2 cups crushed corn flakes over the top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy banana bars
directions: Cream together butter and mashed banana.
Blend in egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1/4 cup milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Stir in 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Spread in well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost while warm with Lemon Icing.

title: nutty clusters
directions: Melt chips in double boiler and add peanuts; stir and spoon onto waxed paper. Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: dutch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands in a big bowl.
Pat into cookie pan 1/4-inch thick and brush with water.
