Sprinkle with chopped nuts and press into dough.
Bake for 20 minutes until nuts are brown.
Cut while warm and cool 10 minutes.
Then remove with spatula.

title: parmesan squash ring
directions: Place onion and butter in medium bowl.
Microwave at High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased baking ring.
Microwave at High for 13 to 18 1/2 minutes, or until set (rotating 1/4 turn every 3 minutes).
Let stand 8 minutes.
Loosen edges and invert onto serving dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top of bread.
Add sausage.
Blend the milk, eggs and mustard and pour over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Blend 1/2 cup milk and soup and pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate banana berry trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed; cool and cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Layer:
1/2 brownies, strawberries, bananas, chopped candy bars and Cool Whip; repeat.
Refrigerate at least one hour. Garnish with additional candy if desired.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Stirring, cook 1 minute after it starts to boil.
Cool to lukewarm and then add vanilla.
Should be enough to ice one cake.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Add instant oatmeal and peanut butter; mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool, then eat.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole(serves 60 people)
directions: Cook,
debone and cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken with
celery,
onion
and
bay leaf.
Cut noodles into 1-inch pieces
and cook in chicken broth and water until done. Add cream
of	chicken
soup,	chopped green peppers, chopped pimento and
cut
up chicken to the drained noodles.
Mix well and divide into 3 greased pans.
Top each with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel
and
cube
potatoes in bite-size pieces.	Combine all other
ingredients	in soup pot with exception of chopped chives. Simmer
slowly
for 1 hour or until potatoes are done and
can
be mashed
lightly
with
spoon or potato masher to thicken
soup. Serve
in individual bowls.
Just before serving, sprinkle with chopped chives.

title: pot roast with gravy
directions: Melt shortening in electric skillet.
Sprinkle meat tenderizer on both sides of roast and pierce with fork.
Rub both sides with flour.
Brown in skillet set at 325° on both sides.
When browned, reduce temperature to high range of simmer.
Cover with vented lid.
About 1 hour into cooking, turn roast and add onion and garlic to top of roast.
Let simmer an additional 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove roast to platter, with onion on top. Remove all liquid from skillet, except about 4 tablespoons. Reserve.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and rise temperature to 350°. Brown flour; add reserved liquid and stir.
Add water to desired consistency for gravy.
Boil 2 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese salad dressing
directions: Add grated cheese as desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar at high speed until blended. Add eggs, one at a time. Add lemon flavoring. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to mixture alternating with sour cream. Beat well. Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hrs.

title: pepper relish
directions: Pour on boiling water; drain.
Cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil, then pour off.
Add chopped peppers and onions; boil for 1 minute, then can.

title: ham-chutney pastries
directions: Combine flour, curry powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water over part of the mixture.
Gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form dough into a ball.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut 3-inch rounds.
Brush edges with milk.
Spoon a rounded teaspoon of ham mixture onto half of each circle.
Fold pastry round over.
Seal edges with fork.
Brush with milk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Cut butter in slices and cover cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish beans
directions: Cook beans until they are done and a small amount of water is left in them; set this aside.
Cut up a large onion and add the meat; cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce.
Add chili powder and enough salt to satisfy your taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: date balls
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, eggs and dates. Cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat.

title: pizza
directions: Make crust according to mix directions.
Spread Contadina pizza sauce.
Layer fried and drained hamburger, sliced pepperoni, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Top with shredded cheeses. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400° until crust is light brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put milk and coconut into a double boiler.
When hot, add flour mixed with sugar.
Add salt.
Cook until thickened.
Just before taking off the stove, add butter.
Take from stove and quickly add the whites of two well beaten eggs.
Pour into ready baked crust. Spread over the top, whites of two eggs well beaten.
Spread thick with coconut and sprinkle with sugar.
Place into oven and brown.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk; blend.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust; chill 3 hours.
Top with fruit pie filling.

title: donut holes
directions: Heat oil 3 to 4-inches deep in pan or deep-fat fryer.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and mace into medium mixing bowl.
Add oil, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water, combine chocolate and 1/2 cup cold water.
Microwave for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until chocolate is melted.
Add gelatine at once and stir.
In the meantime, beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until light.
Add chocolate mixture, salt and vanilla and cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture; pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill, top with whipped cream.

title: taco casserole
directions: In medium size casserole dish, spread half of bag of Doritos over bottom of pan.
Mix ground beef, chili beans and Ro-Tel together. Spread over chips.
Cover with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes 5 minutes; cool.
Peel and grate.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan. In large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, sugar and spices; then add tomato soup, shortening, eggs and water. Mix at low speed until well mixed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl, then mix 4 minutes at high speed. Pour into prepared pan and bake 40 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely before frosting.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line tube pan with wax paper. Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Mix well.
Spread half of dough in tube pan.
Put half of margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon, nut mixture over the batter.
Add remainder of batter and then the remainder of the nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan carefully.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter (just enough to cover the bottom lightly).
Place pineapple in bottom of pan and place the cherries in the middle.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perfect pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk, salad oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Bake on hot griddle.
Griddle is hot when a drop of water propped on it dances.
Use 1/4 cup batter per pancake.
Makes about 10 (3 to 4-inch) pancakes.

title: henry's grilled chicken
directions: Mix vinegar, pepper, salt and poultry seasoning together.
Add wine, then whisk in oil.
Pour marinade over chicken, cover and let stand at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: fruit yogurt shake
directions: Place yogurt, vanilla and sweetener in blender.
Whirl, gradually adding frozen fruit.
Bananas, peaches, blueberries, strawberries or raspberries work best for this recipe.

title: quick company dish
directions: Mix hamburger, chopped onion, eggs, salt and pepper. Crush crackers.
Mix as meat loaf but make into meatballs.
Fry and simmer.
Then pour spaghetti sauce into meatballs.
Simmer.
Cook rice.

title: russian chicken
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Add marshmallows and sugar.
Let stand for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix in whipped cream and celery. Place in greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on pizza pan; bake as indicated. Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing.
Spread mixture over dough.
Put vegetables over mixture, then sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate.

title: divinity frosting
directions: Boil the sugars and water.
Pour slowly over the beaten egg whites. Continue to beat until fluffy. Frosts any 3 layer cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Add soups, beans and seasoning mix.
Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over Doritos in bowls.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, add more flour if necessary. Drop on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 min.
Make frosting of 2 c. pwd. sugar, fresh orange juice, butter, lemon extract and a little hot water if needed.
Frost when cool.
Makes appro. 60 cookies.

title: rice or bread pudding
directions: Mix all.
Dot top with oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
(If adding raisins, place in hot water for a few minutes to soften.) Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's rice custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then add the remainder of ingredients. Fold together thoroughly.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Rice will settle at bottom with a light custard top.
You may omit rice if you only like custard.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
As soon as cake is out of the oven, poke holes all over the cake with handle of a small wooden spoon.
Immediately pour cream of coconut over the cake evenly, then pour Eagle Brand milk over the cake evenly.
Refrigerate until cold.
Spread Cool Whip evenly and sprinkle with fresh coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: crispy italian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine crushed croutons, cheese and seasonings; mix well.
Combine tomato puree and egg.
Dip cut up chicken in tomato mixture, then coat with crouton mixture.
Place chicken in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Serve hot or cold.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine the peaches with 1 cup sugar; let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Place in the oven to melt.
Combine the remaining sugar, flour and milk; pour this over the melted butter. Do not stir!!
Spoon the peaches on top of the batter.
Do not stir!!
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian veggie casserole
directions: In a sprayed baking dish, combine your choice of veggies and enough spaghetti sauce to lightly coat them. Cover and bake at 400°for 20 minutes or until veggies are almost done.

title: apple bread
directions: Pour sugar over apples; let set for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in closed container.
Put 2 teaspoons heaping mixture to 1 cup hot water.
Mix as needed. Makes about 12 cups.

title: beef curry in a hurry
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Blend curry powder and salt into 1 1/2 cups water; add to skillet along with raisins. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Blend flour in 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Gradually stir into meat mixture. Bring to a boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add apple.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Arrange peas and carrots over meat mixture.
Prepare corn bread according to package directions. Fold Cheddar cheese cubes into batter.
Spread over top of casserole or arrange batter to make strips across casserole.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll in pecans (broken up).

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool.
Mix pudding as directed, add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Cut strawberries into pieces, sprinkle with sugar and add glaze.
Tear cake up and layer in bowl or glass dish.
Top with strawberry mixture, then pudding mixture. Continue layering, ending with pudding mixture on top.
Top with strawberries.

title: crawfish loaf
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in butter.
Add all ingredients, except cheeses.
Cook until crawfish is done.
Hollow out and make a boat in the French bread.
Pour mixture into boat.
Top with cheeses.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 375° degrees for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine tuna, cottage cheese, chiles, sour cream, red onion, salsa and noodles.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crackers and cashews together and sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Spread over crackers. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine ingredients, beating well after each egg.
Bake 90 minutes at 300°.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add milk and the remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, milk, 1/2 can onions, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and black pepper together.
Put in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle rest of onions and cheese on top and cook 10 more minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Chop all vegetables very small.
It is necessary to chop vegetables small to stay on pizza.
Blend salad dressing mix and fat-free mayonnaise with softened cream cheese.
Mix and bake pizza dough as directed.
Bake on a greased pizza pan or pan for baking cookies, as directed with mix.
Cool.
Then spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Layer with the vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine in an iron skillet.
Add brown sugar, spread evenly and arrange pineapple rings on top.

title: jiffy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large dish.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add milk and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into the butter. Pour fruit and juice over mixture.
Add additional sugar to taste. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; cook 2 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Add the vanilla.
Pour mixture over the oatmeal and pecan pieces.
Stir rapidly to mix.
Take by tablespoon and cut off with a knife to make small pieces.
Place on waxed paper; refrigerate until solid.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cucumbers and onions. Make sure all are mixed well.
Then add cucumbers and onions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions with butter.
Mix rice, corn and soup and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Cut dough like you would to bake cookies and position on pizza pan about 1/4 inch apart.
Bake as directed on wrapper.
Cool. Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over big cookie.
Slice apples and position on top of cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Save 1 1/2 cups syrup.
Combine margarine, marmalade, spices and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Gently stir in fruit.
Heat for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water and let stand 2 or 3 minutes. Add beaten eggs and oil. Then add dry milk, sugar and salt. Let rise 45 or 60 minutes. Then put on greased pan. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes (depends on your oven). Makes 4 dozen.

title: jimmy jar's chili
directions: Mix together and cook on low heat or crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with corn chips and cheese on top.

title: flitch
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Cream all ingredients together and chill for a few hours.
Roll out like pie dough. Spread with a thin layer of peanut butter; roll like jelly roll. Slice 1-inch thick.
Makes three rolls.
Put in airtight container to keep fresh.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into rolls or balls (can also be chilled in a Jell-O form; first put chopped nuts in bottom). Roll in either chopped nuts or paprika.

title: chocolate gravy(for shirley mccallie)
directions: Combine in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until boiling. Stir quite often to prevent sticking.
Cook until mixture gets a little thicker than syrup.
Serve with hot buttered biscuits.

title: hobo meal
directions: Pat out desired size of hamburger patty.
Place on small sheet of tinfoil.
Place slice of onion on hamburger.
Then place the amount of frozen French fries you desire.
Last, you place string beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Roll up and crease the tinfoil to hold in juices from hamburger.
Cook at 350° until the hamburger is done.

title: mush
directions: Boil water; combine remaining ingredients and add to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Cover; continue cooking
on low for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour into loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices and fry slowly in small amount of hot fat until golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is claylike.
Remove from pan and place on wax paper.
Knead several times and let cool.
Store in a plastic container.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Use asparagus juice, plus milk, to make liquid.
Fold in two beaten egg yolks when sauce is thick.
Fold in two beaten egg whites. Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° until crackers are golden brown.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage; set aside. beat eggs, add milk and salt. into greased 9x13 inch baking dish layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
This is an easy breakfast dish, Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cheese 'n wieners
directions: Split hot dogs to within 1/2-inch of ends.
Insert strips of cheese.
Place hot dog on shortest side of crescent dough triangle.
Roll up.
Place cheese side up on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Melt cheese.
Add picante sauce, soup and meat mixture.
Heat together and serve.

title: chili steak and beans
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and cumin.
Coat beef steak pieces with flour mixture.
Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in celery, onion, carrots, water and chili sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until beef is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Add kidney beans (with liquid) and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until beans are hot and green pepper is crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Can be served over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Fold in broccoli.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 9-inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and oleo.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Prepare pie crust and put one over pecan mixture.
In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into pie crust in pan.
Top with 2nd crust and flute; cut slits in top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cool upright in pan 5 minutes.
Invert onto plate.
Cool 1 hour.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Let all ingredients come to a boil; cook about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Yield: About 25 pints.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as
directed.
Tear into pieces.
Put half of cake into torte bowl or
punch
bowl.
Add	1/2 of the pudding. Add 1/2 of the cherry
pie	filling.
Add
of	the pineapple. Add 1/2 of the Cool
Whip	and
nuts.
Do not mix. These are layers.
Repeat
directions again, layering ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serves 15 or so.
Cut in half for smaller numbers to spoon out to serve.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Pour warm 7-Up over sherbet; stir lightly.
Add ice and serve.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Cook cranberries and lemon rind in
1 quart water until skins pop.
Remove lemon rind.
Strain through food mill or sieve.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Cool.
Add frozen juices and 3 gallons water.
Add chilled ginger ale at serving time.
Yields 100 servings.
Top with orange slices.

title: marinated pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Mix all ingredients well, coating all pretzels.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 1/2 hour at 250°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until thick and bubbly.
Be careful not to let the beans get dry.

title: katie's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and eggs and cook until thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
For pie make 1/2 again and cook longer.

title: nut goodies(cookie bar)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Mixture will be stiff. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients, except flavoring in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water.
Beat for 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add a few drops of flavoring. Mix.
Put on cake.

title: old-fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 234° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball, which flattens when removed from water).

title: mom's apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix at medium speed, beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes.
Scrape bowl with rubber spatula.
Slowly beat in salad oil until well blended.
Reduce speed to low; beat in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and walnuts.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Test.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust of graham crackers and margarine.
Press into large pan or casserole dish.
Drain pineapple and pour over crust.
Make up instant pudding and pour over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped pecans over Cool Whip.

title: christmas crunch
directions: Melt bark in microwave and pour over other ingredients.
Stir until coated.
Pour on cookie sheet.
When cool, about 10 minutes, break apart.

title: jellied fowl(recipe from the 30's)
directions: Cook the fowl until perfectly tender; remove skin and bones and when cool, chop very fine.
Allow broth to cool.
Skim off all fat and boil until reduced to 1 pint.
Add to this gelatin, previously soaked in 1 cup cold water for 5 minutes and stir until dissolved.
Season with salt, white pepper and celery seed.
Stir in the chopped meat and place in small molds.
Cress or parsley with slices of lemon may be used for garnishing.
Very nice for luncheon.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and flaked onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add other ingredients, using tortilla shells.
Make layers in baking dish, alternating with mixture.
Top with grated Longhorn cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple brown betty(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with "Pam." In medium bowl, combine bread and margarine; toss until well coated. Set aside.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and roll into small balls.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs to coat.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Place tomato wedges, green pepper and onion into shallow dish. In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute; pour over vegetables immediately. Cover tightly and chill.
Keeps for several days.

title: good and easy cake layers
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together. Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate flour and milk until mixed; add vanilla. Bake 30 minutes in 350 degree oven. Makes 3 layers or a square.

title: teekranz
directions: Beat together butter, egg yolks and sugar until creamy.
Add milk, flour, filberts and baking powder.
Beat the egg whites and fold in.
Pour in a Bundt form and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or tester comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, margarine and confectioners sugar until almost smooth.
Pat thin into an ungreased 8-inch square pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour meat mixture into 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Grease casserole.
First, top with corn bread batter; spread carefully with wet knife.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: p m s cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box. When still warm, poke holes in cake with handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour milk and caramel over cake. Allow cake to cool and spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle Heath bar pieces on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: easy noodle casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Prepare spinach per package instructions.
Drain well and set aside.
In large skillet brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Mix in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in spinach, cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Blend in noodles.
In 12 x 7-inch baking dish, layer half of meat mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook chopped broccoli.
Drain.
Saute onion in oil until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel dessert or salad
directions: Mix coarsely crushed pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine together; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well and enjoy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together corn, eggs and salt.
Alternate corn mixture with breadcrumbs in layers.
Dot with butter on top and pour in 1 cup milk.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma northern's angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a small bowl.
Add buttermilk to flour mixture; mix well.
Add yeast.
Mix well.
Let stand.
The longer it stands, the better the biscuits.

title: gerwig blackberry cake
directions: Into one bowl, mix together brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolks, butter, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix the blackberries, flour, baking powder, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add this mixture alternately with the buttermilk to the first mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites and bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan, greased and floured.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix sugar with eggs; beat well. Add condensed milk and beat well into egg mixture. Mix the evaporated milk and vanilla with mixture. Pour into gallon ice cream container.
Add plain milk until container is 3/4 full. Mix with long handled spoon. Freeze in ice cream freezer until firm, using 8 to 1 portions of ice and salt.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and peel.
Combine Cheddar cheese, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and melted stick of oleo.
Mix until blended.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: batter for vegetables
directions: Sift flour with salt. Beat eggs and add milk, oil and flour. Beat with beater until smooth.

title: mushroom barley tureen
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt the butter.
Add mushrooms, onions, celery and carrots.
Cook over moderately low heat, stirring often for about 15 minutes.
Stir in flour, then add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Prepare barley separately and drain.
Add barley to pot and stir in milk, chicken, salt and pepper.
Simmer.
Enjoy with a fresh loaf of bread.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Mash strawberries.
Add oil, eggs and flour; mix until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Place in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt with
ice water and cover for 1 hour.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and pickling spice to boiling. Cool.
Add to cucumbers.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and dressing; mix lightly.
Chill 1 hour. Add celery and eggs.
Mix sour cream, onion, parsley, pickle, pimento, mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine with other ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppin' pizza cups
directions: Place a biscuit in each of 12 muffin cups.
Press biscuits up sides of cups to form shells.
Mix beef, sauce, onion and brown sugar and place 1 tablespoon of mixture into each biscuit cup. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: "heart smart" vegetable pizza
directions: In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup flour, yeast, sugar and salt; add water and 2 teaspoons oil.
With mixer at low speed, beat until flour is just moistened.
Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Onto lightly floured surface, turn dough and knead about 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
In greased bowl, place dough, turning over to expose greased portion.
Cover with towel and set aside in warm place to rise for about 45 minutes or until doubled in size.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, onion and salt in Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Boil until half done.
Add vegetables.
Simmer until done. Pour off and save 2 cups water.
Add back in the 2 cups water, cheese, butter, flour, milk and ham.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves approximately 15.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients on medium.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over 8 to 10 quarts popcorn.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, the cinnamon and 1/2 cup of walnuts.
Place apples in bottom of greased 8 1/4 x 3/4-inch round ovenware cake dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients, all at once, and mix until smooth.
Pour over apples; sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 50 minutes or until done.
Cut in wedges.
Serve with cinnamon-topped whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce sweet potatoes
directions: Put sweet potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place applesauce on sweet potatoes.
Mix brown sugar, oats and cinnamon; stir in butter.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken breast until almost done.
Cut or tear into bite-sized pieces.
Place in 8 x 8 x 1 3/4-inch Corning dish. Sprinkle with bacon bits.
In separate pan, under medium heat, mix chicken broth, soup and sour cream.
After this is fully blended, pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add dry ingredients, then apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the morsels and bake for 55 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Fill pressure cooker 1/2 full of water with the first 5 ingredients.
Cook under pressure for 25 minutes. Reduce pressure. Remove meat and dice. Remove bone and put diced meat back in. Add the barley, rice and bouillon cubes.
Cook (no pressure) for 1/2 hour. Add the tomato sauce and water.
Let simmer and then add the spaghetti.
Cook 20 minutes more. Delicious.

title: grandma kreyer's molasses cake
directions: Mix the baking soda in with the buttermilk. Combine the other ingredients in with buttermilk and mix together. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese while cold.
Allow Cheddar and cream cheese to soften.
Using hands, blend all ingredients, except nuts.
Shape into 3 balls, about the size of grapefruits.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: almond cheesecake
directions: Process with chopping blade adding flavorings after sugar and sour cream are thoroughly mixed.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes or until bubbly at edges.
Refrigerate until firm; serve.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and pecan pieces.
Pour filling into prepared pie shell.
Arrange the pecan halves around inside edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.
Best served at room temperature or slightly warm.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix grated cheese and butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Add red pepper to taste.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten each ball with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: hot german slaw
directions: In large saucepan heat all to boiling point.
Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered stirring occasionally until cabbage is crisp and tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients together.
Form into large ball. Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: ardelles easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, egg and salt.
Mix in flour, by hand, until dough is easy to handle.
Place in a well-greased bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator overnight or for a few hours.
Shape into rolls; let rise about 2 hours.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: no-roll pastry shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine oil and milk in cup.
Whip with fork.
Pour over flour.
Mix and press out evenly. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and fill or fill and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° to finish.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Then add peppers, onions and pecans.
Let set for 2 hours in refrigerator and it's ready to serve.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup each of the cheeses. Place in large casserole dish, sprinkle with reserved cheese and bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Crumble into bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Beat remaining ingredients, except cheese, until almost smooth.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pizza-burgers
directions: Put beef and sausage in skillet. Add water and cook at medium heat until browned, stirring constantly to break up lumps.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and place in 6 open-face hamburg buns. Cut cheese in strips and spread on buns. Place buns on cookie sheet and into a preheated 350° oven. Bake for 12 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry soda pop cake
directions: Make cake according to package instructions, and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
After cake has cooled, poke holes in cake with a straw.
Prepare gelatin mix by dissolving gelatin in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add cold Shasta soda (don't let set).
Pour over cake, then refrigerate long enough to set.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups cold milk, and beat until thick.
Stir in cool whip and spread over cake.

title: bacon-fried chicken(from 1975 edition)
directions: Place bacon strips side by side in a shallow roasting pan and set in a preheated 400° oven to bake 10 minutes.
Lift bacon from pan and set aside until later.

title: chocolate ice cream pie
directions: Blend together lightly in bowl ice cream and milk.
Add pudding.
Beat just until mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Let stand in refrigerator for one hour.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine margarine, sugar and water; put in microwave until margarine melts.
Add 1/2 of chocolate morsels and stir until melted; add vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add this to ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining morsels and nuts; mix well.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes; cool and cut into squares.
Doubles easily.
If using 9 x 13-inch pan, add 5 to 8 minutes cooking time.
Freezes well.

title: texas spring salad
directions: Layer half of salad ingredients.
Sprinkle half sugar and cheeses over top.
Using a teaspoon, cover with dabs of mayonnaise (use half of 1 cup).
Layer again.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and cheeses; again, cover with rest of mayonnaise.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Don't toss until ready to serve, then add crumbled bacon.

title: famous cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream brown sugar and butter.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in raisins, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: garlic butter sauce
directions: Beat softened butter and garlic together.
Spread on French bread or Vienna bread. Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in oven.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Divide batter in half.
To one half, add half the Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 cup melted margarine. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Melt caramels, 1/2 cup margarine and rest of Eagle Brand milk.
Add pecans.
When cake is finished, pour caramel mixture over hot cake.
Pour rest of cake batter over caramel mixture.
Return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.
Frost when cool.
Very rich!

title: pizza
directions: Prepare dough as directed on package.
Spread on pizza sheet, then add the sauce. Next put on the cheese.
Then add all the other toppings as you wish.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until crust is done.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread and cool.
Break into pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer other ingredients onto corn bread in order given.
Top with Miracle Whip and sweet pickle juice.
Blend together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: holiday frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water and juice of lemon.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add drained pineapple, dried bananas and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with mixer.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in cream cheese and pudding mixture together.
Pour into pan on cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch crust, reserving 2 tablespoons of crumb mixture for garnish.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Beat yolks until thick and fold into egg white mixture.
Fold in whipped cream, lemon juice and peel.
Pour into crust and top with crumbs.
Chill or freeze.

title: nicky's tapioca pudding
directions: Beat egg white in a small bowl with mixer on high speed until foamy.
Add half the sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Mix tapioca and remaining, sugar, milk and egg yolk in pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir tapioca mixture on medium flame on stove until it comes to a full boil.
Gradually add to egg white mixture, stirring quickly.
Add vanilla.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Place ground beef and sausage in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Pour on Ragu; sprinkle with cheese over sauce.
Mix milk, eggs, oil, flour and salt.
Slowly pour batter over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and salted onions in water until tender. Add pepper, butter and milk and bring to a boil. Serve hot. (Add celery to recipe, if desired). Makes 2 quarts.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Mix together and chill well.

title: egg boats
directions: Let hard boiled eggs cool, Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks, Mix with mayo, salt and pepper. Put yolk mixture back into halved eggs. Cut cheese into triangles.
Insert toothpick into cheese to form a "sail".
Place into egg boat.

title: orange slush drink
directions: Mix and blend in blender until a thick slush.
Serve.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large frypan, cook hamburg and onion.
When done, drain off excess grease.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Put about 1/2 teaspoon oil in each little muffin tin; rub it all around the tin so that they will not stick.
Get the oil hot before the batter is added.
Fill each cup about half full.
Let the Yorkshire get crisp and golden brown.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: settler's beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from frying pan; drain.
In a small amount of bacon drippings, cook ground beef and onion; drain well.
Rinse and drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Place in casserole dish.
Add pork and beans.
Mix sugars and remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked beans and lightly mix together. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Fill a baby food jar 1/2 way full of whipping cream.
Shake, shake, shake until solid butter forms, about 10 to 15 minutes. Pour off the buttermilk.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Blend.
Let set 4 to 6 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew
squash and chopped onion together and drain well. Mix together
soup,
sour
cream and cheese and add squash and onion. In	a
skillet, melt stick of oleo and add 3/4 package of herb dressing
and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of this into squash mixture. Pour all into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes
or until bubbly and hot.
Last 5 minutes, add remaining dressing mixture on top and bake just until browned lightly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: presbytery chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, margarine and mustard.
Put herb stuffing mix in blender and process into fine crumbs.
Dip chicken breasts into mixture and roll in herb stuffing mix.
Place in a shallow ungreased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil for the last 10 minutes to brown chicken. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot pineapple juice; let set until syrup-like. Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to pineapple juice/Jell-O mixture.
Whip Milnot; add to mixture.
Place vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom of pan; add mixture.
Sprinkle top with vanilla wafers and refrigerate.

title: choco-cherry brownies(microwave)
directions: Microwave (High) butter in uncovered 1-quart bowl 45 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Stir in cocoa and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Grease bottom only of 8-inch square dish. Sprinkle with cherries. Cover loosely with plastic wrap.

title: delicious dip for vegetables
directions: Prepare a vegetable tray with green onions, zucchini, yellow summer squash, radishes, mushrooms, celery, green peppers, carrots, small round tomatoes, etc.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Chill vegetable tray.
Serve after chilled.
Recipe will feed several.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Place beef in a Dutch oven.
Combine all remaining ingredients except rolls; pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours, turning beef occasionally.

title: 350.00 dollar chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, oats (powdered in blender), salt and baking powder.
Mix creamed and dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, melted chocolate and nuts.
Place golf ball size or smaller on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a full boil.
Add a thick paste, made with the cornstarch and water.
Cook and stir until very thick.
Fold in the fruit.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in water.
Drain and mash.
Add soup, pimentos, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of stuffing mix into large baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture over top.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mrs. gill's congo bars(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Melt margarine in saucepan and stir in the brown sugar.
Mix well.
Let cool, then gradually beat in the eggs, one at a time. Add flour mixture, nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: quick potatoes for potluck
directions: Mix all ingredients; fold in egg whites last.
Season to taste.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or more at 325°.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs thoroughly.
Spread in buttered 9 x 10-inch pan and smooth it out.
Chill in refrigerator at least one hour.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate 20 minutes and cut into squares.

title: rotelle salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salt and oil; rinse under cold water and sprinkle with milk to moisten.
Combine onion, tomatoes, peppers and pickles in small bowl and set aside.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, beef broth, vinegar, pickle juice and dill weed.
Mix into macaroni, keeping a small amount of sour cream mixture in reserve.
Add vegetables and refrigerate for about 1 hour.
You can add reserve to moisten just before serving.

title: cobbler
directions: Pour into baking pan that contains 1/4 pound melted butter. Over this, pour canned fruit (don't stir) and add 1 cup water. Bake at 350° until it rises to top and browns.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
Lay onion slices on top.
Cover and bake at 425° for about 3/4 of an hour or until chops are cooked through.

title: rice-stuffed peppers
directions: Thoroughly mix rice, onion, sausage and 1/2 cup cheese.
(May add 1/2 teaspoon ground red pepper.)
Generously stuff peppers with rice mixture; top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut beef cube steak into bite size pieces.
Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat until hot.
Add beef; cook and stir until brown.
Add beef broth and apple juice; bring to a boil. Add frozen vegetables, squash and basil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Makes four 1 1/2-cup servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 3
hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Mince pimento.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
For creamy pimento cheese, prepare in a food processor.

title: championship cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first six ingredients and mix well.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add to potato chip mixture and mix well.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet allowing space for cookies to spread.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, eggs and sugar until creamy. Then mix flour, tartar and baking soda. Gradually add to moist mixture. Dough will be a little stiff. Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball and then roll dough ball in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Peel onions; remove seed from peppers.
Chop and measure all vegetables.
Dissolve salt in 8 cups water.
Pour over vegetables and let stand one hour.
Drain.
(If too salty, rinse and drain again.)
Mix vegetables with sugar, seed and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Bring to a boil.
Pack, boiling hot, into hot jars; seal at once.

title: cherry (or cranberry) apricot muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, place egg, milk, sugars, oil and orange peel.
Beat well 1 minute.
Add to flour mixture and beat about 15 seconds to combine.
Do not overmix.

title: basic refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, oil and sugar in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water.
Add yeast, egg, half of flour and beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Grease top of dough as needed; shape into small balls. Dip in melted butter; place 3 rolls in each section of greased muffin pan.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in bulk. Heat oven to 425° and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 18 rolls.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix melted butter, peanut butter, vanilla and sugars together. Pat into a pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons butter in a pan and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate and then cut into squares.

title: curry cawsway(burmese)
directions: Combine chicken, onion, ginger, garlic, salt, turmeric, red pepper and oil in saucepan.
When chicken is done, stir in coconut milk and 2 cans of water.
Mix graham flour with enough water to make it a soupy consistency.
Add to curry.
Serve over cooked spaghetti and garnish.

title: basil broiled chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat broiler.
Squeeze lemon over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place chicken, skin side down, on a broiler pan.
Broil chicken 8-inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Turn; broil for 5 minutes longer.

title: ruth's orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix jellos with water.
When well dissolved, add sherbet and mix well.
Chill a few minutes in freezer or refrigerator.
Take out and add fruit and sour cream, folding them gently.
Put in molds or whatever.
Serves 12.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add baking powder to the milk, then alternately add the milk and flour.
Beat well.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla flavoring and lemon flavoring.
Beat well. Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in a cold oven.

title: margo's chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool, debone and break into small pieces.
Place all ingredients into a large pot.
Season to taste.
Cook on low to medium heat for 1 hour.
Use the chicken stock also to thicken, if desired.
Mix some cornstarch with water and stir into chicken stew slowly.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix together sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
In another bowl, mix together grated cheese and onion.
Heat tortillas in oil. Fill with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over and roll.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine crumbs, garlic and cheese.
Dip shrimp into egg and then crumbs.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake 5 to 10 minutes, until shrimp curl.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and extract.
Add beaten egg yolks, then flour and fruit alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Grease and
flour
loaf
pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Put small pan of water on shelf below.

title: chicken 'n orange salad
directions: Using a food processor, coarsely chop chicken, celery, pepper and onion. Transfer to large serving bowl. Add oranges and mayonnaise and mix. Serve over crisp salad greens with sliced almonds.

title: pasta and sausage soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or soup pot, brown the sausage.
Add the green peppers, onions and garlic, cooking until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and their juice, breaking up with fingers, macaroni, sugar, Worcestershire and the chicken broth.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 12 cups or 8 main-dish servings, 420 calories per serving.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well. Add flour and sugar. Add milk, a little at
a time, and vanilla.
Mix well. Add melted butter.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes, until firm.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add sugar.
Cream butter and Crisco.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Add flavorings.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Whip the first 5 ingredients together; set in refrigerator until firm.
Put 1/2 mixture in graham cracker crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling into middle, then cover with remaining mixture. Sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs on top.
Blueberry filling is also good.

title: european cake
directions: Mix together and bake in moderate oven, 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Have baked pie shell ready.
Cook first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly until thick.
Add jello, food coloring and almond flavoring; cool.
Add strawberries.
Stir to coat.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
Add Cool Whip and garnish with sliced strawberries.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon.
Do not sift.
Add to sugar mixture.
Beat well, adding orange juice.
Stir in pecans, coconut and apples.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes. Glaze while hot.
Punch holes in cake before glazing.

title: kelly squares
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bread).
Trim crusts from bread.
Take three slices of bread and generously frost like a layer cake, including sides.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Repeat this for the whole loaf of bread.
Freeze for at least 1/2 hour. Remove from freezer and cut each piece into 9 pieces.
Bake on greased sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: the wrobel's pizza bread!!!
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Drizzle olive oil.
Sprinkle on seasonings. Stack vegetables on top.
Put more olive oil and seasonings.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Broil in the oven until bread is crunchy and cheese is bubbly. Slice and enjoy!

title: mushrooms stuffed with sausage
directions: Mix together sausage, wine, onion, Parmesan cheese, salt and butter.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Continue to bake until cheese is melted.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate 24 hours and bake at 325° for 1 hour or you can barbecue, also.
You may substitute any kind of meat.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, water, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours for easier handling.
Heat oven to 375°.
Using about 1 tablespoon of dough, press dough around each candy wafer to cover completely.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Top with walnut.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken broccoli quiche
directions: Thaw broccoli in cold water.
Mix together in bowl; broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion.
Blend in blender; milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Put broccoli mix in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Pour Bisquick mix over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake until melted.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and butter.
Remove from heat when well blended. In large mixing bowl, combine marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread on wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: hominy tamale pie(from the rainville kitchen)
directions: Mix cornmeal, hominy, oil, salt and water.
Boil and stir 3 or 4 minutes until thick.
Cool.
Line large casserole with mixture.
Reserve some for top.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture; mix well. Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes, turn out on wire rack to cool.

title: lemon delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter, and confectioners sugar.
Press in a 8-inch by 8-inch by 2-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch edge.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes more.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: In large pot, cook hamburger, onion and green pepper until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, chili powder, salt and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and corn.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in microwave for 5 minutes; stir. Continue in microwave until melted and smooth.
(I use jalapeno cheese for extra hot and spicy Queso.)

title: inside-out chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt, tube or streusel pan.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Pour into
a
34-cup percolator the apple cider and the ginger ale.
Place
into
the
percolator basket, the cinnamon candies, 2 sticks cinnamon and the 24 cloves.
Perk and serve hot.
Makes 30
cup)
servings.
This punch is not only delicious, but the fragrance is wonderful.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Let stand about 2 hours, then drain.
Add hot pepper, salt and vinegar.
Let come to a boil, then can.

title: apple ginger chutney
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients, except apples. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add apples and simmer 15 to 20 minutes more or until most of the liquid is evaporated and sauce coats the back of a spoon.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Use this over fish or poultry.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Equal parts grape jelly and chili sauce.
Heat.
Put wieners in and serve warm from a chafing dish.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Double recipe for 3 regular pies.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Drain 1 can of lima beans.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake in covered casserole for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious with ham.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Peanut butter or nuts can be added.
Use square baking dish greased with butter.
Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Add milk gradually.
Bring to bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
When this comes to a rolling boil, reduce heat.
Do not stir.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball when small amount is dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Add vanilla.
Add peanut butter and nuts, if desired.
Cool.
Beat until thick and pour into dish.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Pour melted butter over bread; mix well and set aside.

title: strawberry brownie sundaes
directions: For each serving, place a scoop of ice cream on top of a brownie.
Top with strawberry pie filling.
Garnish with chocolate and nut.
Can use chocolate syrup (optional) or butterscotch, raspberry, blueberry, cherry or any topping.

title: corn salad
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over corn, beans, etc., while hot. Put in refrigerator to marinate.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, then add corn syrup, salt, vanilla and liquor. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar together.
Let sit overnight.
Next day, add eggs and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until desired consistency.
Put in jars when cool, then refrigerate.

title: roast beef with coke
directions: Place meat in roaster.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Add mushroom and onion soup.
Pour Coca-Cola around meat (not over) and bake, covered, at 350° for about 4 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots the last hour of baking time.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli in bottom of greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch dish. Make a layer of chicken pieces.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs and drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in baking dish and top with cornflakes mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hebel's potato chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; chop olives to taste.
Chop green onions to taste.
Add milk and stir together to blend smooth.

title: bread 'n butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cucumbers or squash. Bring to a boil.
Add sliced cucumbers or squash.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Keep stirring until cucumbers or squash change color. Pack in jars and seal.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 35 minutes or until brown.
Cool before serving.

title: potato puff
directions: Make fluffy mashed potatoes.
Beat in well beaten egg yolks, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes, orange juice, milk, sugar and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Beat at high speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and flour; cut in margarine with a fork.
Stir in pecans and sprinkle mixture over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: diamond gems
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla. Work in flour gradually.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool three minutes and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool on rack.
Dust again in sugar.
Good for Christmas time.

title: shrimp with spaghetti
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in skillet.
Saute bell pepper and onions until soft.
Add shrimp.
Cook on medium heat until done (3 to 4 minutes).
Do not overcook the shrimp.
Add seasoning while shrimp is cooking.
When shrimp are done and all seasonings added, turn off heat and add 1/2 stick butter.
Mix well.
Add drained spaghetti and mix well.
Serve immediately.
(This recipe called for 2 sticks of butter originally, but I have cut it down.
If you end up with more spaghetti than shrimp mixture, you can add more butter.)

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar, cream and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cook in double boiler until smooth and thick. Stir constantly.
Cool.
Whip 1 cup heavy cream.
Combine fruit mixture, warm mixture and whipped cream.
Chill 24 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Place milk in double boiler; heat to scalding.
Slowly add cornmeal and whip with beater until smooth.
Add butter and cook for 20 minutes.
Separate eggs.
Add beaten yolks and baking powder to mixture.
Beat egg whites until they peak; fold in. Pour into well-greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Too rich for high cholesterol.)

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan, except vanilla. Bring to a boil and cook until forms a soft ball, 238° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until thick. Spread on warm cake.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix in order given.
Set mold on folded cloth in pan of hot water, one inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand a few minutes.
Invert on hot platter.
Serve with cheese sauce or grated cheese.
Fill center with asparagus or other vegetable.

title: poor boy's dinner
directions: Wet possum and roast in hot oak ashes.
Then remove and pick hair off possum.
Roast in ashes again to remove excess hair and fuzz.
Wash possum thoroughly to remove all ashes and cut it up. Place possum in boiler, large enough to hold, and cover with water.
Add salt, black pepper and red pepper. Boil until tender.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Boil beef until done.
Drain and chop beef.
Add sauce and mix.

title: raspberry-topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust, bake 30 minutes.
Spoon raspberry mixture evenly over top.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Spread with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring at least 3 times during baking.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Drain.
Cook noodles until almost done.
Drain.
Mix together hamburger, noodles and sauce.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, onion, celery, parsley, seasonings and enough water to moisten.
Spread stuffing on steak and roll like a jelly roll.
Brown roll in Crisco; when roll has been browned on all sides, add water.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix together Italian dressing, soy sauce and garlic; marinate chicken overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans well.
Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Also good as muffins.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Put beef in crock-pot.
Pour a little Kitchen Bouquet over beef and add enough water to cover beef.
When the beef is done, drain juice off beef into a big cooking pot.
Add more water, bring to a boil and add noodles.
Cook until noodles are done and water has cooked down.
Add beef cubes and soups.
Mix together and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate cake
directions: In a pan, bring cocoa, oleo and water to a boil; remove from heat and cool slightly.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in the cooled chocolate mixture.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: plum kuchen
directions: Sift flour; add butter and cut to resemble fine meal.
Beat yolks; add water, lemon and sugar.
Add to flour.
Stir to blend. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut and arrange plums.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, sprinkle with sugar.
Can use apples; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place a piece of butter on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Combine in double boiler.
Stir until thick.
Add whipped cream when using.

title: scalloped potatoes with sweet marjoram
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow casserole dish.
Layer 1/5 of the potato slices and season with 1/4 each of other ingredients except cream. Repeat layering 3 times.
Top with a layer of potato slices.
Combine cream with 1/2 cup water and pour over potatoes. Cover dish with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours, then uncover and bake 30 minutes until browned.

title: date roll
directions: Crush graham crackers, chop dates and pecans and cut up marshmallows.
Combine in a large bowl; add cream and work together.
Form this into a roll and put in icebox.
This can be kept for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: mexican cheeseburger
directions: Combine cheese, chili powder, mustard and salt.
Place 1/3 cup of mixture on each of 3 thin hamburger patties.
Top with remaining patties and seal edges.
Place on cold broiler pan and broil until done, about 15 minutes, turning once.

title: meringue
directions: Beat water and egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar, still beating.
Add sugar one tablespoon at a time.
When last of sugar is added and blended well, you can put on top of pie and place in oven on broil and brown to golden brown.

title: tater nugget dish
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large saucepan, brown ground meat, onions and celery until beef is cooked. Drain well. Stir in soups, garlic powder, pepper and green beans. Spoon into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Top with potato nuggets. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and potato nuggets are golden brown.

title: peach salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Mix in all ingredients. Place in refrigerator and allow to congeal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour until smooth.
Add half and half and simmer until thickened.
Pour drained corn in baking dish. Pour sauce over corn.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: You can omit nuts or use peanuts.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
In a saucepan, bring the next 4 ingredients to a boil and pour into dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir the rest of the ingredients into the mixture.
Pour into an ungreased cookie sheet (pan with sides, 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
As soon as cake is done, spread icing on cake while hot.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Put the broth, asparagus, 1 teaspoon chives in a pot, boil until asparagus is done.
Put into a blender on liquify then add the soup.
Blend again for second or two, put back in the pan and add the milk.
Heat until hot.
Then add the other teaspoon of chives.

title: my mother's nut bread
directions: Mix nuts, raisins, water and baking soda together.
Mix eggs, sugar, baking powder and flour together.
Combine both mixtures and bake for 1 hour in a slow oven at 350° in loaf pans.

title: world's finest chocolate bar pie
directions: Melt candy and add 12 oz. Cool Whip.
Mix. Pour onto crust. Add 8 ounce Cool Whip for topping. Freeze for 10 minutes.

title: hulda dessert
directions: Make the first 3 ingredients into a crust and pat into a 12 x 9-inch pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine spaghetti and butter. Place half in the bottom of a casserole dish. Top with half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Put remaining spaghetti in dish and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares and top with spaghetti sauce.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: In sauce pan, heat sugar, oil, and vinegar until sugar is dissolved; remove and cool. Mix veggies together and pour cooled dressing over and toss. Can be refrigerated for 24 hours. Toss occasionally during this time. You may add spiral pasta to veggies if desired.

title: amaretto
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vodka, extracts and food colorings; mix. Ready to use.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings in sauce for 24 hours covered with plastic wrap.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain. Add the kidney beans. Add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese with the Doritos chips. Mix the dressing and Tabasco sauce to taste.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Heat milk; stir in shortening, sugar and salt and cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
After milk mixture has cooled, stir in yeast mixture; stir in flour.
Knead dough until firm and smooth.
Let rise to double size.
Punch down and shape into individual rolls.
Rub thin coating of shortening on outside of roll and place in baking pan.
Let rise to double size.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.
Makes about 40 rolls.

title: aunt jenny's frozen salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot pineapple juice.
Stir often while cooling.
Whip jello.
Whip the cream and cheese together.
Stir in rest of fruit.
Pour into pan and freeze.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Bring water to boiling point.
Add to meal and stir until mixture is to the consistency of stiff grits.
Wet hands.	Take heaping tablespoon of mixture and roll into ball about size of a golf ball.	Flatten and drop in hot oil.
Cook to golden brown. Serve hot.	Serves 4.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cube corned beef.
Cube cheese.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper and onion.
Pour over noodles and corned beef.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in large bowl.	Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until it bubbles.

title: cornbread(pun do maiz)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all together until smooth.
Heat a 9-inch iron skillet with oil and sprinkle cornmeal over the bottom (about 2 tablespoons cornmeal).
When pan is hot, pour in the batter and bake in the oven until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In shallow baking dish or pie plate (large), combine all ingredients except pepperoni and olives.
Top mixture with pepperoni and olives.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers, fresh veggies or nacho chips.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in the baking pan or dish. Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Mix well and pour over melted butter.
Next, pour fruit in pan over the top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup sugar in a mixing bowl. In a saucepan, boil 1 cup sugar, margarine, shortening and cocoa. Pour over flour and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: really good cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add mincemeat.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie tin.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: In bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix flour,
sugar, oil, pineapple, cinnamon, pecans and egg yolks together.
Fold
in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oriental mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms parallel with stems.
In large skillet cook and stir onions in butter until tender.
Stir in mushrooms. Sprinkle flour over mixture and stir until mushrooms are coated. Add water, cube and soy sauce.
Stir until cube is dissolved. Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Mix well, make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain. In a large bowl, combine pasta, salad dressing and Salad Supreme seasoning.
Toss in vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours. Stir before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese roll bake
directions: Lay
rolls side by side (the two strips make a sheet of dough).
Wrap rolls around cheese and bake until brown or done according
to directions on rolls.	Serve while warm.
(Excess dough
can	be trimmed and made into flowers, etc. to decorate top.)

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir to mix well.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers or chips.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: easy rice dessert
directions: Cook rice.
