Let cool, then add cherries, pineapple and whipped cream to your rice; refrigerate.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Mix sugar and marshmallows in pan.
Cook over low heat and stir until sugar has dissolved.
Cook on high until it boils. Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
Pour over nuts and chocolate, butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts.

title: german butterscotch cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While cake is still hot, with fork punch holes all over top of cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on cake.
Now while cake is still hot pour butterscotch topping on cake.
Let cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip on cool cake.
Crush Heath bars on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, beaten yolks, grated rind, juice and milk.
Mix well.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish; set in pan of hot water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves four.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding ingredients in order given, blending well after each addition.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross, and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on rack before storing in tightly covered can.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in slow oven (325°) until light brown.
Fold sugar and salt into egg whites.
Beat until stiff peaks form, then fold in nuts.
Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, or until nuts are coated with a brown coating and no butter is left in pan.
Cool.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook, stirring, for 3 minutes, or until chicken is white. Remove chicken.
Add broccoli, red pepper and chicken broth; cover and cook until broccoli is tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add bow ties and cheese; toss until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german balina
directions: Make batter the night before.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat milk and shortening; let cool to warm stage.
Add flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Beat well.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, add eggs one at a time, beating well, then add half and half.
Batter will be thin.
Let mixture stand 30 minutes.
Pour 1/4 cup into heavy frying pan over moderately high heat.
Roll pan so that dough runs edge to edge. Turn before batter looks dry.
Put on platter and brush with melted butter between pancakes.
Serve with syrup.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare zucchini, onion and carrot.
Boil in pan until just tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine sour cream and soup. Mix well; set aside.
In another bowl, put complete contents of stuffing mix and add melted butter.
Mix together well.
Set 1/4 to 1/2 cup aside to sprinkle on top.
When vegetables are tender, drain.
Put all ingredients, except topping, in a large bowl. Mix together with a spoon.
Pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute peppers in margarine.
Mix in cooked broccoli, cheese, 1 c. of the bread crumbs, eggs and salt.
Put into greased baking dish, then add mushroom soup and bake at 350 degrees until bubbly. Add the remaining bread crumbs to the top and brown.

title: roast-beef salad(serve this main dish salad with crusty bread.)
directions: Put lettuce, beef, corn and scallions on a serving platter. Sprinkle with dressing and pepper.
Carefully toss to mix and coat.
Surround with tomatoes and cucumber.
Serve more dressing alongside, if desired.

title: broccoli goldenrod
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water just until tender. Drain and set aside. Combine next 4 ingredients in a saucepan, and heat thoroughly. Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with egg yolk.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown onions until light brown.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and dill, then combine with rice.
Steam cabbage and remove thickened part.
Place ball of rice mixture into the cabbage leaf, then roll as for a bundle, push ends in.
Put in a baking dish, cover with tomatoes (1 can) and a little catsup.
Add 1 cup water. Bake for an hour at 350°.
This is a traditional Christmas Eve dish in many homes.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Shape ground beef into 50 meatballs.
Place in shallow baking pan and broil until browned.
In saucepan, cook onions and peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place meatballs in Dutch oven and pour mixture over them.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion to ground beef until tender.
Place Velveeta and other ingredients in crock-pot.
Keep warm.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: sicilian soup
directions: Chop onion and brown with sausage.
In a big pot mix other ingredients.
Drain sausage and add to pot.
Simmer.
Add cooked rigatoni 30 minutes before serving.

title: swiss chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon.
Add all remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: sweet pickled cantaloupe
directions: Peel and seed cantaloupes; cut into 1 1/2 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch pieces to make 1 gallon.
Dissolve salt in 2 quarts water.
Add cantaloupe; let stand 2 hours.
Drain and rinse cantaloupe; set aside.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream white sugar with butter, oleo and brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop with spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan. Sift flour, soda and spices into mixing bowl; set aside.
In blender, put remaining ingredients; blend on high until smooth. Pour into dry mix; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: yankee bean soup
directions: Pick over beans; wash thoroughly.
Place in large kettle; add water.
Cover.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 1 hour.
Add ham bone, sliced onion, celery leaves and mustard.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are soft but unbroken.
Melt butter in skillet; add chopped onion and carrots, cook 6 to 7 minutes, until beginning to brown, stirring constantly.
Add with tomatoes, salt and pepper to beans.
Cover.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until beans are partly broken and have slightly thickened the soup.
Remove ham bone.
Cut meat from bone and add to soup.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: Mix together potatoes, corn, tomatoes and water.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Over low heat, add milk and cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
(You can add a dash of hot pepper sauce if you want a hotter soup.)
Makes 2 quarts.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Melt oleo in
a
heavy skillet.
Add chopped celery and onion. Cook until
tender.
Add broth, liquid smoke, rice and salt. Bring to a boil.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can	be made
a
day
ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Crush crackers and add 1/2 cup sugar, nuts and dates.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add the sugar and baking powder and mix well.
Fold this egg white mixture into the crackers, dates, etc. Add flavoring and pour into a buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, a little at a time. In a separate bowl, mix crumbs, pecans (broken into pieces) and vanilla, a little at a time.
Combine all these ingredients and place in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool, then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hors d'oeuvres meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet with sides or on grate and broil turning once.
Can be baked at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick company cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost immediately.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla. Beat until well combined.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and nuts. Pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool, frost and enjoy!

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and oleo.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Mix other ingredients and put on top of mixture.
Chill.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer in order as listed.
Bake covered 1 hour at 250°.
(Slow cooker 5 to 6 hours.) Serves 6. Serve with green salad.

title: crispix delights
directions: Put chocolate chips and oil in a bowl in the microwave for 1 1/2 minutes, then add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour over cereal and nuts, stirring until coated.

title: caesar salad
directions: *Pour boiling water over egg and let sit 2 minutes.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Slice white part of leek.
Cook with chopped onion in oil. Boil potatoes until soft and mushy.
Drain potatoes.
Place onion-leek mixture and cooked potatoes in food processor or blender and puree.
Add chicken broth and reheat.

title: cheese stuffed shells
directions: Layer 1 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan. Cook shells according to package. Mix cheeses, bread crumbs, parsley and egg; then stuff into cooked shells. Layer stuffed shells in pan on top of sauce. Pour rest of sauce over shells and top with remaining cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and peppermint flavor until blended. Gradually add powdered sugar and knead until no longer sticky. Divide into four equal portions.
To each portion knead 1 drop of food color.
Shape into 3/4 inch balls, then roll in sugar. Flatten balls with tines of a fork.
Let mints dry at room temperature.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks with waxed paper between layers or cover tightly and freeze up to 2 months.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Layer ingredients, beginning with Oreos, then pudding, then sour cream mixture and end with Oreos.
Really cute with silk flowers stuck in the "dirt"!

title: ladyfingers cream cheese cake
directions: Beat sugar, cheese and 1/2 pineapple, drained.
Add Cool Whip, rest of pineapple and 1/4 cup juice; mix with spoon.
Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers (sides and bottom).
Pour mixture in pan and refrigerate.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix the brown sugar, mustard and flour.
Slowly add vinegar, lemon juice, rind, water and raisins.
Cook over low heat until it thickens to desirable consistency.
Stir frequently.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thoroughly wash chicken, inside and out; pat dry.
Place 2 teaspoons salt in chicken cavity.
Add large pinch of rosemary to cavity.
Salt and pepper chicken on all sides.
Place in a bread loaf pan to which have been added the giblets.
Roast 1 1/3 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown
onion
in butter; add ground
beef.
Cook
until done, then mix all other ingredients with ground	beef and mix well. Pour into casserole dish.
Spread cheese
on top.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Put potato rounds on bottom of oblong dish and around sides. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef and drain.
Place beef, broccoli and 1/2 the onion rings in dish.

title: slaw
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage.
Let stand in the refrigerator 2 or 3 days.
Will keep for weeks.

title: chicken polynesian
directions: Combine chicken and salt in deep saucepan, in water to cover. Simmer until chicken is tender; drain, reserving stock.
Bone chicken and cut in small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, 1/2 cup of stock and curry powder; blend well.
Place layer of chicken, green beans, water chestnuts and onion rings in greased casserole.
Top with soup mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spanish style chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown chicken in hot shortening. Add onions and garlic.
Cook onions until brown but not burned.
Add tomato juice and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add rice and remaining broth. Simmer and cover for 20 minutes.
Add peas and pimento. Simmer for 5 minutes more or when the peas are done.
Serves 6 people.

title: easy chicken
directions: Put chicken in frying pan.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over it good.
Put on high to start it cooking, then cover and simmer on medium heat until done.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add enough broth for desired consistency.
Spoon into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: great grandmother's pancake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour desired amount on hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles cover the surface.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers; put in 1/2 cup salt (either canning salt or plain salt, not iodized) and water to cover cucumbers. Let stand 3 hours.
Combine all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drain cucumbers from salt mixture and place in vinegar solution.
Bring to a boil again.
Put in jars.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid, then bring to boiling.
Dissolve jello in boiling liquid.
Let cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale, then chill until partially set.
Blend in pineapple, cranberry sauce and marshmallows.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish and chill until firm.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin slices. Combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce with sugar, ginger and garlic. Stir in beef. Let stand 15 minutes. Remove flowerets from broccoli; cut in half if large. Combine remaining cornstarch and soy sauce with 1 cup of water. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or large skillet over high heat. Add meat and stir-fry 1 minute; remove. Heat remaining oil in same wok. Add broccoli, onion and carrot. Stir-fry 4 minutes. Stir in meat and soy sauce mixture; bring to a boil. Cook until sauce thickens. Grab your chopsticks and serve immediately.

title: taco platter
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Dice lettuce, tomatoes and sliced onions.
In pizza size pan, layer cream cheese, ground beef, taco sauce, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and Cheddar cheese.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread into a pan.
Batter will be thick.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour over batter.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and bean soup
directions: Cook together carrots, celery, onion, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except for cheese.
Pour half of batter into well greased skillet.
Put grated cheese on top of batter in skillet.
Pour remainder of batter on top of cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: oriental soup
directions: In a medium saucepan over high heat, bring water and bouillon to a boil.
Add noodles, carrots and ginger root, reduce heat to low and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes or until noodles and carrots are barely tender.
Add shrimp and green onions; simmer 2 minutes or until shrimp are heated through.
Add spinach and simmer for 1 minute or until spinach is tender.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in 2 cups finely chopped nuts. Refrigerate, covered, at least several hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Mix butter, flour and seasonings together over medium heat until smooth.
Add ketchup and sherry.
Next add milk.
Cook until thickened and add shrimp.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: french beef casserole
directions: Blend flour and seasonings into butter.
Slowly stir in bouillon and gravy coloring.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add beef, onions and lima beans. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Combine cheese and parsley and sprinkle over casserole before serving.

title: hamburger hot plate
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Salt and pepper.
Use 1/4 teaspoon garlic, if preferred.

title: quick crust
directions: Mix together and press into pie plate.
Dough will be real buttery (oily).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl (but not foamy), then beat in shortening and sugar until creamy in texture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Blend well.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to shortening and sugar mixture and beat well.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for two hours.
Add a banana before serving.
Serves ten.

title: lemon tea cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Grease and line a loaf pan with paper. Pour in batter and bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.
When done, spread immediately with mixture of lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar. Cool before slicing.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; boil, then dice or cut in slices.
Put potatoes in large bowl.
Add celery, onions, pickles and pimiento.
Mix together the mustard and French dressing; pour over the vegetables.
Add salt and pepper, then mix well.
Chill until serving time, then mix mayonnaise.

title: black bean spirals
directions: Beat cheeses, sour cream and onion salt until well blended. Mash or blend the beans well.
Spread a thin layer of beans over tortilla, then a layer of the cheese mixture.
Roll up tightly and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: little nothings
directions: Spread with preserves, jam or apple butter (anything thick enough to spread).
Roll up and freeze overnight preferably.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix this together and cook until thick.
Cool until cold. Then put your drained strawberries in and fold in.
Pour into your baked pie shell.
Put Cool Whip on top and let set about 3 hours in the refrigerator before cutting pie.
Very good!

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or when light brown.
Remove from oven and let cool. Combine cream cheese and sugar; mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture on baked cookie dough.
Cut up fruit and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes more.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add milk in which the baking soda has been dissolved.
Put in the vanilla, salt and flour; mix well.
If dough is too sticky, add a little more flour. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dust cookie roller with flour or powdered sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until slightly brown, in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove insides of peppers.
Immerse in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
In skillet, cook meat and onion until brown and tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice, Worcestershire, basil, water and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup cheese.
Fill peppers with meat.
Place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with remaining meat.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Stand 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: escalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Cook onion in 3 teaspoons butter until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, cheese and carrots. Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Toss stuffing in 1/2 cup melted butter, sprinkle over top.
Place in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Re-sift flour with baking powder.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in finely chopped walnuts.
Cover and chill.
Roll out on light floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press a walnut half or piece on each cookie.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes until edges are very lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp scampi primavera
directions: In large stir-fry skillet, place oil, shrimp, garlic, butter, celery, chopped broccoli, tomatoes, bell pepper, parsley, salt and lemon pepper.
Stir-fry until shrimp are pink and vegetables are tender, but not soft.
Add wine.
Stir-fry for five minutes total. Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: baked sausage and mostaccioli noodles
directions: Make hamburger balls and brown. Add water after they brown. Cut up white potatoes.
Add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and let cook.
Cook in electric skillet or just a saucepan over the stove.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cook 4 to 6 apples to desired thickness and measure 1 1/2 cups into bowl.
At once, add shortening, sugar and raisins.
Stir gently a couple of times and then let cool.
Sift dry ingredients and mix carefully into applesauce mixture.
Gently add nuts.
Turn into square cake pan and bake at 350° for approximately an hour. Good plain or with cream cheese or brown sugar frosting.

title: pork chops in sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: Trim extra fat from chops; grease pan with fat and brown chops well on both sides.
Drain fat from pan.
Mix chicken bouillon and water and add cornstarch, then add remaining ingredients except green pepper.
Add bouillon mixture to chops.
Cover pan and cook slowly for about 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Remove stems and seeds from green pepper and add, cooking for 5 minutes more, uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: marinated sirloin tip roast
directions: Put roast and beer in roasting bag overnight; turn a couple of times before you go to bed. Put roast in roasting pan. Mix beer and oil and rub on roast. Then rub roast with dry ingredients. Roast at 325° for about 1 hour 50 minutes to 2 hours, basting frequently. It is done when it registers rare on thermometer. While roasting, make marinade.

title: orange beets divine
directions: Drain canned beets.
Discard liquid.
If fresh beets are used, cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Cover with cold water. Slip off skins.
Cut beets into slices and set aside.

title: sidney's cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add eggs and milk and beat with spoon until mixture is just moist.
Beat in cream and melted butter (do not overbeat).
Pour batter into 8 1/2 x 11-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 1 minute.
Pour into sterilized bottle or jar.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add salt and pepper.
Let come to a bubble.
Add flour and stir well until bubbly again.
Add milk. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese, stir until dissolved.
Butter dish.
Layer a layer of macaroni, then cheese, then sauce.
Layer again.
If sauce on top looks too thick, add a little milk.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and 1 tablespoon of salt; shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown on all sides in hot butter.
In 3-quart casserole dish, mix remaining ingredients plus salt.
Arrange over balls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: williamsburg punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve hot.
Great on a cold night; especially nice at Christmas.

title: sees fudge(makes 5 pounds)
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil, boil for 9 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Spread.
Let cool and cut.

title: oyster dressing(from the files of mrs. john (ola) garner, sr.)
directions: Cut each oyster into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; stuff fowl or bake in greased casserole as a side dish.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water until yeast dissolves.
Add 1 3/4 cups of milk (or potato water), sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix in flour until mixture leaves the side of the bowl.
Remove bread mixture to a floured surface and knead until it is elastic.
Put dough into a 3 or 4 quart greased bowl, cover and let the dough rise for 1 hour.
Punch dough down, cover and allow it to rise for 30 minutes more.

title: georgia corn bread dressing
directions: Brown finely chopped celery and onion in butter.
Crumble corn bread and dried bread.
Add egg and enough stock to make semi-heavy batter.
Add celery, onion and hard-boiled eggs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save 1/2 cup of the broth.
Layer chicken in baking dish.
Mix the next 5 ingredients; pour on top of chicken.
Add chips and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick garlic cubed steaks
directions: In a saucepan melt butter and stir in Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, parsley & garlic.
Brush butter mixture on both sides of steaks.
Place steaks in a wire grill basket.
Grill over hot coals for 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn basket over and grill for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Season steaks with salt & pepper.
Place each steak atop a toasted bread slice.
Spoon remaining butter mixture over steaks.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beet salad
directions: Measure beet juice and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring this to a boil. Remove from heat. Add gelatin, sugar, vinegar and horseradish.
Stir and add beets.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: braised turnips
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a nonstick skillet and saut over low heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broth and next 2 ingredients; cover and cook over low heat 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and half the flour, beating until smooth with electric mixer or dough hook. Next, add eggs, shortening and the rest of the flour, mixing until the right consistency.
Let rise in refrigerator, punching down until dough stops rising.
Make out and let rise 2 hours before serving time.
Bake in 450° oven.

title: hazel's chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together in large saucepan.
Pour in oil and cream.
Cream together with whisk.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour in mixing bowl and beat with mixer for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: fresh frozen corn
directions: In a large pan mix the ingredients.
Heat to boiling point. Boil 5 to 15 minutes.
Set pan in ice water to cool.
When cool, put in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt butter and cook onions in it until tender.
Butter a casserole dish.
Line with cracker crumbs.
Add layer of onions, then layer of soup until dish is full.
Beat eggs and add in milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add a few more cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: peach crunch
directions: Mix sugar and egg.
Gradually add flour; set aside.
In a a 9 x 11-inch pan, put peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle flour mixture on top of fruit.
Pour melted butter across the top.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cut up bacon in pieces; fry.

Fry or brown 1/2 chopped onion. Cut up potatoes into squares; boil. Discard water. Add whole milk or half and half to cover the potatoes. Add clams. Add bacon and chopped onions, butter, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate 2 hours or overnight.
Use 1/4-inch strips of beef or chunks of chicken.
For kabobs, use meat, mushrooms, peppers, onions and water chestnuts.
Broil 12 minutes, turning frequently. Baste with marinade.

title: parmesan meatballs
directions: Mix the first 11 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add water, a little at a time, if needed, to moisten the mixture.
Moisten your hands and form the meat mixture into meatballs.
Brown the meatballs in butter over medium heat in a wide skillet.
Turn them often as they cook.
Rotate the meatballs from pan center to pan edge as they brown.
When all the meatballs are browned, carefully pour off the excess fat.
Turn the heat to medium-high.
Add the seasoned tomato sauce to the skillet and return the pan to the heat.
If you do not have a seasoned tomato sauce on hand, add a pinch or two of garlic powder, basil, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper to a few cups of canned tomato sauce.
The meatballs are ready to serve after they simmer 15 minutes in the sauce.
Turn them a few times while they cook in the sauce.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in chafing dish until warm.
Serve with crackers.

title: "bingo" sandwich spread
directions: Grind the cabbage, pepper and onion in food grinder, using coarse blade.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 500°.
Put first four ingredients into brown paper grocery bag.
Cover bottom of baking pan with oil. Shake chicken pieces in bag to coat with flour mixture.
Arrange in single layer in pan.
Sprinkle with rosemary and more paprika. Cook 20 minutes at 450° to 500°.
Turn and cook 20 minutes at 325°.
Turn and cook another 20 minutes at 325°.

title: hush puppies
directions: In
a
medium
bowl,
combine all dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg
and milk.
Mix well.
In a deep fat fryer, heat 4 inches
of oil until hot.
Fry hush puppies, a few at a time, until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pork chops in orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Arrange onion rings over each chop.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over pork chops; cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes until pork is tender, basting occasionally.
Garnish with orange slices and fresh parsley.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix water, jello and frozen strawberries.
(It will be syrupy.) Slice cake in pieces and line bottom of pan with 1/2 of cake.
Pour 1/2 mixture over cake.
Put another layer of cake and then rest of mixture.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: quick and yummy vegetables
directions: Stir together melted butter, crumbs and almonds. Set aside. Combine all vegetables and stir well with soup to coat. Pour into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Spread crumb mixture evenly over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: nut cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and oleo.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture with milk and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake at 375°.

title: short ribs of beef
directions: Brown ribs thoroughly in heavy Dutch oven, pouring off fat as it accumulates.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, onion, celery, marjoram, thyme, wine, bouillon and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until fork-tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove short ribs and keep warm.
Blend butter with flour, then stir into pan juices.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring now and then.
Serve gravy over short ribs.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it spins a long thread or hard ball stage.
Add salt and peanuts.
Cook until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add quickly butter, vanilla and soda.
Beat well.
Pour into buttered shallow cookie sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: pear relish
directions: Chop pears, onions, peppers and celery.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and turmeric, then add chopped vegetables and pears (mix and let stand overnight).
Heat to boiling point and seal in sterilized jars.
Put in cold pack cooker, heat in water bath 20 minutes.

title: peach trifle
directions: Crumble half of pound cake; layer in bottom of large glass bowl.
Put half of vanilla pudding on top, then half of peaches, half of Cool Whip and sprinkle almonds.
Repeat layers (pound cake, pudding, peaches, Cool Whip and almonds).
Arrange a few peach slices on top.

title: herbed chicken bake
directions: Prepare rice, using package directions.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown slowly in butter.
Spoon rice into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with chicken.
Add soup to skillet.
Slowly add Sauterne wine, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then turn over chicken and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: mexican squares
directions: Slice Jack cheese in bottom of greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Lay chilies on top of cheese. Mix Bisquick and milk together and pour over chilies. Beat eggs together and pour over milk mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 300°. Add salsa to top and bake another 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 5-10 minutes. Cut into squares. 8-10 servings.

title: beef supreme
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomatoes (cut up), Pizza Quick sauce and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare noodles according to package directions and drain.
Combine noodles, sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
Stir well.
Spoon half of noodle mixture into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 big servings.

title: broccoli-stuffing bake
directions: In saucepan, heat milk.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Slowly add hot milk to eggs.
Add stuffing croutons, broccoli and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 350° until golden brown.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate). Cut a thin slice from the stem end of each pepper.
Wash outside and inside. Remove all seeds and membranes. Cook peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes. Drain.

title: meal-in-a-bowl chicken soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a 4-quart saucepan over high heat. Add carrots and celery.
Reduce heat; simmer until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add peas, corn and chicken; simmer about 5 minutes longer until tender.
Stir in macaroni and parsley.
Heat through. Makes 2 quarts.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Prepare crust as instructions on package.
After cooking crust, spread sauce evenly.
Crumble beef and sausage evenly. Tear ham into pieces and place on top of meat.
Add onion, pepper, olives and mushrooms.
Then place pepperoni evenly.
Spread cheese evenly over top and bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each water chestnut.
Secure with wooden pick.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour teriyaki sauce over the appetizers.
Let stand for at least 30 minutes; drain.
Place on a roasting rack.
Microwave at High for 8 to 9 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Makes 18 appetizers.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Combine all other ingredients. Cook 15 minutes in pressure cooker.
Let pressure drop off at its own accord.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin, sugar and salt.
Add briskly boiling water and stir until all ingredients are dissolved.
Stir in cold water, vinegar, lemon juice and pepper sauce; chill until partially set.
Fold in cabbage, celery, green pepper and olive slices.
Pour into a 5 1/2 cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Serve on bed of lettuce with mayonnaise and trim with carrot curls, ripe olives and parsley.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate at least 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Quarter dates.
Add soda and pour on boiling water.
Cool. Cream shortening and add sugar until blended.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour once before measuring. Sift flour and salt together and add alternately with date mixture.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Use well-greased pan and bake in moderate oven 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove and add jello.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell. Pour mixture over strawberries.
Top with whipped cream before serving.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in applesauce.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix soda and water, then add to batter.
Pour into greased and floured cupcake tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to beaten eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in baked pie shell for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Microwave sugar, Karo and water for 6 minutes.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Microwave additional 5 to 6 minutes, stirring several times with wooden spoon.
Pour into 2 beaten stiff egg whites.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes.
Fold in 1 teaspoon vanilla and pecans.
Choose day with less than 40% humidity.

title: hopi fry bread
directions: Get a large bowl and mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir water into dough just enough to make soft.
Shape dough into 16 egg-shaped balls.
Roll each ball until 1/2 inch thick.
Put shortening in 13-inch skillet. Fry 3 or 4 pieces at medium until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onions and chopped eggs.

title: chicken tamale bake
directions: Combine
broth and corn meal in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Whisk in 1/2 cup of picante
sauce.
Reduce
heat
to low; cook until very thick, whisking occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin spice bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil until blended. Combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, ginger and cloves; add to pumpkin mixture just until combined.
Stir in cranberries.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and flour.
Mix butter with sugar. Mix together and top peaches with mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in butter.
Add sweet potatoes and milk; beat until mixture is coarse in consistency.
Gradually add water.
Knead until dough is smooth. Roll out to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Use sharp knife and cut into 3-inch squares.
Place squares on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Remove to rack.
Use spatula or knife to put on sheet.
Serves 6.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Pout 1 1/3 cup boiling water over broccoli; add rice.
Mix cheese, soup, celery and onion together.
Stir into rice mixture. Add melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie plate; place all ingredients in blender and blend at 10 speed about 2 minutes, stopping to scrape sides.
Pour into plate; bake 45 minutes or until puffy and center is dry.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Combine yogurt and preserves.
Fold in whipped topping.
Serve with fresh fruit or cubed pound cake.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill for at least 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, onion, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crushed cornflake crumbs with 1 tablespoon butter.
Brown for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Put romano cheese in a food processor with metal blade.
Turn motor on and drop garlic through feed tube to mince.
Stop machine and add spinach, artichokes, cream cheese and eggs.
Process until thoroughly blended; turn into a medium bowl and fold in mozzarella.
Transfer to a 2 to 3 cup baking dish and bake until heated through, about 20 to 25 minutes. Serve hot with your favorite tortilla chips, crackers, and/or crusty French breads or rolls.
Serve sour cream and salsa on the side.

title: simple mexican bean dip
directions: Put bean dip and cream cheese in a dish and microwave to soften.
Mix together and spread thin in dish.
Put sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze water out of spinach.
Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Chill dip 2 hours or more.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak 1 to 2 inches thick.
Mix flour, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Pound into steak.
Brown meat and onion in hot fat. Add tomatoes.
Cover; cook over low heat, or bake in moderate oven (350°) until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugars and flour. Add beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cottage cheese muffins
directions: Blend liquid ingredients.
Mix together dry ingredients and combine.
Then add cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
I use juice from pineapple if necessary to produce right consistency for muffins.
Batter should be thick; don't overstir.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In double boiler, combine cornstarch, flour, 1 3/4 cups sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Gradually add water, stirring until smooth. Over medium heat, boil 1 minute until shiny and translucent. Quickly stir some hot mixture into egg yolks and then blend back into pan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix cookies with butter.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough on pizza pan (flatten out like pizza dough).
Top with fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with more fruit on top.

title: french green beans and cheese
directions: Saute onions in butter and add mushrooms to brown a little. Add remaining ingredients; stir constantly while heating.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol phelp's world's best cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat well and add oil.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork; bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix sugar, onion, pepper, ketchup and mustard with beans.
Put in baking dish; lay bacon across top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook 20 minutes more.

title: chilitos - easy!
directions: You don't need to measure anything.
This one will always turn out!
Heat chili on medium heat.
Add as much cheese as desired. Stir until all cheese is melted. Spoon into warm tortillas and roll up.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Roll out crust and place in bottom of pie pan.
Layer apples and sugar mixture until pie is heaped high with apples.
Dot with butter and put top crust on this.
Poke holes in top crust.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add the pepper and onion; cook, stirring often until onion is soft.
Add the ground beef, breaking into small bits.
Cook until brown.
Stir in corn and salt to taste.
Mix well.
Place in a baking dish.
Cover with tomato slices and sprinkle the crumbs over the top.
Bake 25 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: zesty fruit refresher
directions: Mix all the juices and place in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, place 1/2 cup fruit juice mixture into glass tumbler and fill rest of glass with ginger ale.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Brown beef in large skillet, stirring to crumble; drain.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 1 hour. Serve on buns.
Yield:
8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in 4 quarts of boiling salted water to which 1 tablespoon of oil has been added.
Cook for 15 minutes, then drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix Ricotta cheese with beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Cover the bottom of a shallow 3-quart casserole, 13 x 8 1/2-inch in size, with a small amount of sauce.
Alternate layers of noodles, Ricotta, noodles, shredded egg and sauce, ending with noodles.
Top with a layer of Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle it with a little sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until heated and lightly browned on top.
Remove from the oven and allow to stand for 10 minutes in a warm place before cutting into squares.
Top with a generous amount of sauce.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Add pineapple juice to hot potatoes and beat until smooth. Using 1 marshmallow for the center of each ball, roll marshmallow in sweet potato mixture.
Then roll in crushed corn flakes until well coated.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tennessee mountain cornbread
directions: Work buttermilk, flour, corn meal, soda, baking powder and salt into sausage.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°.

title: teriyaki steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak.
Pour sauce over round steak and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Barbecue steaks on grill.

title: sour cream pecans
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix the sugar, sour cream and salt. Bring to a boil and cool, stirring until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in very cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat until the mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Add the nuts and stir quickly to coat on all sides. Turn out on a greased cookie sheet and separate with 2 forks.
Can stir in 1 teaspoon cinnamon when ready to heat mixture.

title: toffee bars
directions: Beat shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and oats.
Beat well and pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun catfish(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Cut catfish into small thin pieces. Mix hot sauce with mustard; dip strips in this mixture and let marinate 2 to 4 hours. Dip in corn meal and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: strawberry blueberry jam
directions: Stir sugar into strawberries and blueberries.
Set aside 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Stir fruit pectin and water into saucepan.
Bring to a boil on high heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir pectin mixture into fruit mixture.
Stir constantly until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy, about 3 minutes (some sugar crystals may remain).
Pour into clean plastic containers to within 1/2-inch of tops; cover.
Let stand 24 hours.
Jam is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerator or freeze extra containers. Makes about four 1-cup containers.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
May add box of red raspberries at serving time if desired.
Also may add other fruits.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook 5 pounds of
baking potatoes until tender, about 40 minutes.
Drain, then mash well.
Beat together cream cheese and sour cream; gradually beat into mashed potatoes until smooth. Beat in garlic salt and pepper. Turn mixture into a buttered, shallow 3 to 4 quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover and chill up to three days.
To reheat, bring to room temperature. Cover and bake in 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: moon cake
directions: Heat water to boiling and add margarine, salt and flour all at once.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: cereal candy
directions: Mix cereal, marshmallows and walnuts together in bowl. Melt chocolate; pour over mixture. Drop by spoonful quickly onto wax paper. Let harden.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put berries in oblong type greased baking dish, approximately 6 x 11-inches, and cover with pineapple. Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Serve topped with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mexican taco dip for a crowd
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Add salsa, pimentos, taco seasoning, cheese and hot sauce (to taste).
Mix all ingredients together and spread in a serving dish with sides at least 2-inches high.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cook brown sugar and water until a small amount tested in cold water forms a ball.
Pour onto beaten egg whites and flavor with vanilla.
Beat until stiff and drop from a spoon.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Add other ingredients by hand.
Put mixture into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scandinavian potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes into 1/2 inch cubes.
Mix together with apples and pickles in medium bowl.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, mustard and salt until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and stir gently to coat evenly.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan.
Beat all ingredients until smooth; pour into pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes until done; cool 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: To serve, fill cup half full with mix.
Add hot water and stir.

title: cranberry cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, honey and cinnamon until smooth. Cover bottom of serving dish with this mixture. Stir cranberry sauce until spreading consistency, then spread over cream mixture. Sprinkle with almonds. Cover and refrigerate 2-3 hours. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender at one time.
Blend until mixed.
Pour into 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all until ball forms.
Roll into smaller balls with hands. Press onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and salt together and set
aside.
Add
to
mixture
of pumpkin, water, soda and flour and
bake.
Grease
wide mouth jars with Crisco.
Do not flour. Fill
jar
half full with dough and bake.
Bake at 325° for
one hour.
Put
lids
on and seal or dump out and freeze. Makes 8 pint jars.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, pineapple, raisins and lemon juice.
Mix yogurt and mayonnaise; add sugar and blend until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over carrot mixture and toss until well coated. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Just before serving, toss again and sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 2 servings; 187 calories per serving and 176 grams sodium.

title: sweet 'n spicy sauce
directions: Mix everything together in a pan and cook on low heat.
May be used to baste a ham every 1/2 hour or serve as a sauce over ham at the dinner table.
Very tasty!

title: egg pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in an iron skillet, pouring in enough to barely cover the bottom of the pan, turning pan to coat. When dry around the edges, turn over.
Serve with sugar and cinnamon or grape jelly.
Serves 3.

title: corn flake chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter. Top with corn flakes and butter.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake in moderately slow 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan; place right side up on rack to complete cooling.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cube and boil cabbage for 10 minutes; rinse twice in cold water.
Put in buttered dish and top with shredded or cubed cheese and cubed bread.
Then mix cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: *Half of a quarter-pound stick.

title: chicken with pastry
directions: Cook chicken in 3 cups water with onion, celery and 1 tsp. salt until tender over medium heat.
Remove from broth and debone. Cut into large chunks and place in bottom of greased 9 X 12 baking dish.
Remove celery and onion from broth.
Blend 4 Tbsp flour with 1/4 c. water and gradually whisk into simmering broth. cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour enough sauce over chicken to just cover.
Preheat oven to 375.

title: oreo lush
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mix pudding and milk.
When thoroughly combined, add cream cheese and whipped topping.
Mix well on medium speed.
Layer crumbled Oreos with pudding mixture in a glass 8 x 10-inch dish.
A few mini Oreos can be used to garnish the top.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot margaritas
directions: In 4-quart, nonmetal container, combine apricot nectar, lemonade concentrate, tequila, brandy and ice.
Cover.
Freeze until of slush consistency, about 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Heat in saucepan and boil about 1 minute.
Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts on graham crackers. Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Heat about 10 minutes at 375° or until mixture bubbles.
Let cool and then break into pieces.

title: circle 3's sweet sour chicken
directions: Mix preserves, dressing and onion mix.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Wash, peel and slice apples thin. Mix flour, sugar, salt and spices.
Combine with apples and place in pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° for 30 minutes (9-inch pie).
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice to apples if they are not tart.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and hamburger in fat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer 1 hour, adding water if necessary.
Add beans and heat.
Serves 8.

title: grilled chicken with indian spices
directions: In a small bowl, combine vinegar, oil, onion powder, garlic, coriander, ginger, cumin, salt and pepper.
Using fork, pierce chicken liberally on both sides.
Place in a resealable plastic bag or on a pie plate.
Pour marinade over chicken; turn chicken to coat and seal bag or cover plate with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 10 minutes.
Preheat broiler or heat charcoal until hot.
Place chicken breasts on rack in a broiling pan or over grill of hot coals.
Broil about 3 inches from heat until chicken is no longer pink, about 4 to 5 minutes per side, brushing frequently with marinade.
Serve with steamed rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: Place hen in large baking pan and brown well.
Brown duck and sausage in Dutch oven.
Meanwhile, fill a large gumbo pot half full of water.
Boil on high.
Add onion soup mix, onion and roux (about 1/2 pint, depending on how dark you like your gumbo). Drain meat well and add to gumbo.
Add salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste.
When meat is almost cooked; add parsley.
Serve over hot rice.
Feeds a gang!

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan cheese and pepper in a clean, small paper bag.
Pour melted margarine into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread to cover bottom of pan.
Cut potatoes into quarters lengthwise.
Moisten potatoes in water.
Place potato quarters, a few at a time, in paper bag with flour/cheese mixture.
Shake to coat, place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for one hour, turning once.

title: angel wings
directions: Skin chicken breasts; season with salt and pepper.
Pour 1/4 cup broth over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and add to milk, oil and vanilla.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to blueberries.
Combine liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moist.
Fold in blueberries.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Cook together sweetened condensed milk and dates until thick, stirring frequently. Add the chopped nuts. Spread on the Ritz crackers. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: low-fat chicken marsala
directions: In large skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly.
Add chicken and cook until both sides brown.
Add scallions and cook until softened.
Add wine and cook until liquid becomes slightly syrupy.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with grated onion.
Fold in shrimp.
Pour onto serving platter and top with bottle of cocktail sauce. Easy!
Serve with crackers.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: *Can be adjusted to taste.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients to beaten eggs.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese stuffed chicken breast
directions: Place a ham and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end.
Secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides. Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Cut slice from top of bread; remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite-size pieces; reserve.
Brush insides of shell with 3 tablespoons margarine, melted.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crab or shrimp puffs with hot sauce
directions: Combine Bisquick, cheese, onion and crab.
Combine egg, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to crab mixture, stirring to blend. Drop by teaspoon into 1-inch of oil heated to 375°.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain and serve with hot sauce.

title: ham and corn skillet breakfast eggs
directions: Brown ham in butter.
Add corn, pepper and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until eggs are set.
Turn off heat.
Stir in cheese.

title: yogurt broiled chicken
directions: In large bowl with spoon, mix yogurt, green onion, oregano leaves, olive or salad oil, white wine vinegar, salt and pepper. Add chicken breast halves; toss to mix well.
Let halves stand for 15 minutes, turning them occasionally.
Preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Place chicken breasts on rack in broiling pan.
Place pan in broiler at closest position to source of heat; broil breasts 4 minutes.
Turn breasts; brush with remaining yogurt mixture and cook for 5 to 6 minutes longer until chicken breasts are fork-tender and lightly browned.
To serve, arrange chicken breasts on warm, large platter.
Garnish with oregano or parsley sprigs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilly dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with fresh vegetable or chips.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add onions and simmer for 10 minutes.
Do not let get brown.
Mix noodles, margarine and onions.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, 1/2 noodles, 1 cup of each cheese, all the potatoes, rest of noodles and cheeses.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Let set for 5 minutes and serve.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally in thin slices about 2 inches long.
Heat oil in skillet or wok (medium heat).
Put garlic and meat in skillet and brown.
Add vegetables, salt, pepper and ginger. Cook until tender.
Combine cornstarch, stock and soy sauce. Add to skillet and bring to boil until thick.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add cream last.
Drain cranberries and pineapple before adding to mixture.
Otherwise, it will be too soupy.

title: cake mix brownies
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, shortening and about 1/2 the cake mix until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining cake mix, chips and nuts.
Bake in ungreased oblong pan in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Mix and marinate meat for at least 2 hours or overnight. Bake uncovered at 300° for about 1 3/4 hours. Turn meat or baste every 1/2 hour. Add water as needed.

title: apple cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll apple up in dough and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over apples.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Drizzle margarine over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish with half bag of stuffing mix.
Mash down on bottom of dish.
Cook squash and onions; add soup and rest of ingredients.
Layer over dressing mix.
Top with cheese and rest of dressing mix.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan and spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly. Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans and drizzle melted margarine over cake.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cooled.
Very rich!

title: daine's lemon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in the cold water; leave for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, hot water and sugar; cool.
Refrigerate until mixture starts to gel (but not completely gelled).
Whip the egg whites until foamy and stiff, then whip through gelatine mixture.
Combine both, mixing them well.
Put in a serving dish; refrigerate for an hour or more.

title: country chicken vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine broth and rice. Over medium-high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally. Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and butter together.
Pour into baking pan, pour peaches over mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tomato egg snacks
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on crackers or toast.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball or log.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: nut macaroons
directions: Mix nuts, salt and sugar; add unbeaten egg white, working it in well; add more nuts if mixture seems thin.
Roll into tiny balls (size of nickel) and place on a cookie sheet greased with butter.
Bake at 300°
for 20 minutes.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 24 to 36 cookies.

title: cajun pistolettes
directions: Saut onions, bell pepper, celery, green onions and garlic in butter over medium heat until translucent. Add evaporated milk, Velveeta, water, seafood and seasoning. Cook on low until just heated through. Cover and keep warm. Fill a deep frying pan with vegetable oil about halfway. Heat oil. Fry pistolettes until they are browned, turning if necessary. While still hot, holding fried pistolette in a potholder, make a slit in one end. Stick a spoon inside and twirl it around to make some room inside the roll. Using a spoon, stuff with seafood mixture. Eat immediately.

title: skillet salmon steaks and sauce
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add steaks and cook lightly over moderate heat.
Add wine, lemon juice and pepper.
Bring to a boil and then simmer, uncovered, until the salmon flakes easily with a fork and is opaque.
Transfer to a heated plate in low oven.

title: waikiki banana bars
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, flavorings and bananas in mixing bowl; beat hard.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While warm, cut into squares and remove from pan.
Mix powdered sugar and cinnamon. Gently roll warm bars in mixture.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in rice, chicken, soup, milk, 1/2 the cheese and onion, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: homemade root beer
directions: You will need a 40-quart new plastic container (garbage can).

title: golden rice
directions: Chop and brown onion.
Add rice and margarine.
Stir until rice starts to brown.
Add spices.
Put in pot; add chicken broth. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Also great with cooked chicken added before it comes to a boil.

title: reindeer casserole(renskavpanna)
directions: Heat a skillet with the margarine.
When the foam subsides, add the frozen meat.
Gradually separate the meat slices as they cook.
Fry until nicely browned.
Add the chopped onions and cook together with the meat for a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir in the cream and mustard.
Simmer for
a few minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve hot with boiled potatoes and vegetables.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water; boil five minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Add to raisins and stir until clear. Remove from heat and add vinegar and butter.
Cool slightly.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Cover with top crust or lattice strips. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend butter and cheese; stir in flour.
Cover; chill 1 hour. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut in 3-inch rounds with scalloped cookie cutter.
Pat in 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Lay bread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, then layer cheeses, bacon and mushrooms.
Mix eggs, milk and salt; pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Save a little grated Cheddar cheese to sprinkle on top before baking at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal sugar cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients.
Add shortening,
eggs
and
vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Form
into
small balls.
Dip tops in additional granulated sugar.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in a large bowl.
Let egg whites warm to room temperature about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 300°. Grease 10-inch tube pan.
With an electric mixer at high speed, beat egg yolks with shortening and margarine until well blended. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add extracts and beat until well blended.
At low speed, beat in flour (in fourths), alternately with milk (in thirds), beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut and beat until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
With wire whisk or rubber scraper, fold whites into batter until well combined.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add flour.
Add syrup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: beef-noodle soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef and onion; drain. Add tomatoes, beef broth, mixed veggies, salt, black pepper, sugar, celery seed and oregano, if using. Let mixture come to a boil; add noodles. Reduce heat and cover. Let cook on medium-low for 15 minutes, until egg noodles are tender.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
With a whisk, stir in flour, salt and milk.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and carrots. Cook over low heat (do not boil), stirring occasionally about 25 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add pepper and salt to taste.

title: apple-cranberry crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish, combine apples, cranberries and granulated sugar. In a medium bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, flour and pecans. Sprinkle oat mixture over the fruit. Dot with butter. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until fruit is tender and topping is browned. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add garlic, green pepper and carrots. Saute briefly.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, sherry, vinegar, sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: plain  pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flours and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture along with milk and vanilla.
Pour into deep tube pan which has been well greased and floured.
Place in 350° oven and bake 1 1/2 hours without opening the oven.

title: chicken and dumplings(a southern favorite)
directions: Prepare chicken for cooking.
Cook in large pot with water, salt and bouillon cubes.
Simmer until tender.
Remove meat from broth.
Debone chicken.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; make balls and place on a cookie sheet or broiler pan and place under broiler.
When brown, pour off grease and cover with 1 can of mushroom soup.
Heat in oven at 250° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: strawberry jello dish
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pack down like a crust and bake for 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: aunt fern's lo-fat baked beans(serves 12 to 14)
directions: Use crock-pot on low or bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown the ground chuck with 1/2 medium onion chopped fine. Drain excess fat from meat.
Mix in the beaten eggs, 2 cups cooked rice, and add seasonings
(sprinkle) such as salt, pepper, parsley, basil, garlic powder, and oregano to taste.
Wash peppers and cut tops off and remove core.
Stuff with rice and beef mixture and bake 1-1/2 hours in 350 oven.
In separate saucepan melt butter, add flour, let brown and thicken.
Add sugar and tomato sauce and the tomato sauce can of water.
Cook together, and pour over peppers and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix batter according to directions on the box.
Put the pineapple with juice into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Add the cherries.
Pour the cake batter over the mixture.
Melt butter and pour over the cake batter.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: kathy fiore's chile
directions: Saute beef, bacon, onion and garlic.
Add salt, pepper, bell pepper, jalapeno peppers, spices, tomatoes, beans, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk together.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: spicy beef supper
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in water, macaroni and barbecue sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese. Sprinkle with additional cheese if desired.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter; add vanilla.
Place in pan; refrigerate until set.
Cut and enjoy!

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together milk and egg; add oil.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture. Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased muffin pans half full. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a preheated 425° oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: crushed pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; add dry ingredients.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet.
Cook in moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put piece of cherry on top if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: countryside cabbage
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, melt butter; saute onion until soft.
Add cabbage, apple, orange juice, salt and bay leaf; mix well.
Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally 1 1/2 hours until liquid is absorbed and cabbage is tender.
Just before serving, stir in orange sections.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach florentine
directions: Cook spinach per directions on package. Drain well. Mix sour cream and soup mix. Add to spinach. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a pan.
Cook until vegetables are done, about 2 hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend
shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in salad dressing and mayo to mixture until well blended.
Cool and serve.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place raw stew meat and raw vegetables in casserole.
Pour soups and water over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken diable
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine or butter in shallow pan.
Stir in honey, mustard, curry powder and salt.
Add chicken; coat with sauce and bake 1 hour, turning once.
Baste frequently until chicken is done and glazed.

title: orange, pineapple salad
directions: Mix oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O. Drain all fruit.
Mix all together and refrigerate several hours.

title: butter cream bars
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, butter, 1 egg and nuts. Press on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs until smooth. Mix in sugar. Pour over crust mixture. Bake in a 325° oven until done or lightly brown on top, about 30 minutes. Save about 1/4 cup of sugar to sprinkle on top of bars.

title: scalloped tuna-potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes, then drain.

title: crock-pot hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer vegetables in order given in crock-pot, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Top with ground beef.
Mix soup with one soup can water in bowl.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit cobbler(peach)
directions: Combine milk, flour, salt, baking powder and shortening.
Roll out dough.
Place half of dough in a 9-inch square pan.
Cook fruit, butter, sugar and flour until thick.
I use double boiler. Pour this filling on dough.
Place remaining dough on top. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can use any fruit including blackberries.

title: peanut butter pieces
directions: Place butter in large bowl; microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
When butter is melted, add sugar, crumbs and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch dish. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Put chocolate chips in large bowl; microwave on 50% power for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir several times while cooking.
When melted, spread over peanut butter layer.
Chill; cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: pork tenderloin with gravy for 2
directions: In a small container, combine the first five ingredients until blended; set aside. In a large skillet, brown pork in oil on all sides. Stir in gravy mixture, mushrooms and onions. Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until meat juices run clear and vegetables are tender. Serve over rice. Serves 2.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and peanut butter.
Set aside.
Mix flour, salt, soda and oats.
Mix shortening mix and flour mix together.
Roll into round balls and crisscross with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, checking the last few minutes.

title: raisin squares
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, flour, oats, soda and salt.
Put half of this in bottom of pan.
For filling, cook raisins, sugar, flour and water until thick.
Add vanilla.
Put on top of 1/2 oats in pan.
Put rest on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chinese ting-alings
directions: Melt butterscotch drops in a double boiler until soft.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let harden.

title: surprise pumpkin cake
directions: Mix; pour into glass pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over all. Also 1 cup chopped nuts and dribble 1 1/2 tablespoons melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: banana-peanut butter dog biscuits(dog treats)
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
Stir together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the egg, banana and peanut butter.
Blend well with a pastry blender until peanut butter and banana are about the size of small peas.
Add the water gradually, stirring with a wooden spoon.
The dough should be very stiff; if not add a little more flour.
Knead the dough with your hands to create a smooth texture.Roll the dough 1/4 inch thick. (It helps if the "top" and "bottom" of the dough are lightly floured.)
Use a cookie cutter to cut out the biscuits.
Place the biscuits about 1/2 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for about 40 minutes to one hour.
The biscuits should be lightly browned and they should not be moist inside.
Turn the oven off and let the biscuits stay inside without opening the door for five hours, or overnight, to let them harden.Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen 3-inch-long by 1-inch-wide biscuits.
tags: whole wheat flour(may substitute with unbleached flour

title: crab dip
directions: Put in bowl and mix together.

title: brajalas
directions: Pound round steak very thin.
Prepare stuffing made from toast (grated), chopped onion, chopped celery, chopped hard-boiled egg, salt, pepper, garlic, oregano and Worcestershire.
Spread stuffing on steak; roll lengthwise and tie securely.
Cover with tomatoes and sprinkle with seasonings.
Add 1 cup water to baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; uncover and brown 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: party cookies
