directions: Mix lemon cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Will be stiff.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Press flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crock-pot meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce, grape jelly and mustard in crock-pot; stir well.
Cover and cook on high setting while preparing meatballs.

title: chocolate gravy n' biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Set aside.
In medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt the margarine.
Remove from heat. Add cocoa and stir until smooth. Add milk and sugar mixture.
Return to heat.
Stirring continually, cook until thickens, like a gravy or sauce. Remove from heat; add the vanilla. Serve over fresh hot biscuits or open-faced grilled ones. Or even serve over ice cream and cake.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Use electric beater to mix.
Roll into a ball or log shape.
Chill.
Before it becomes too firm, you can roll in walnuts or parsley.

title: mixed berries with sauce
directions: Set aside 1 pint raspberries for sauce and combine rest of the berries in large bowl. Combine the pint of raspberries with the sugar in a blender for 30 seconds. Combine the cream cheese and yogurt in bowl. Beat until smooth with wire whisk.
To serve, spoon some raspberry sauce onto each plate.
Place some of the berries over the sauce and top with a heaping tablespoon of cheese mix.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish orange cake
directions: Grind raisins, walnuts and orange rind.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add the beaten eggs.
Fold in dry ingredients, alternating with sour milk. Add fruit, nuts and flavoring.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Pour over hot cake in pan 1/2 cup sugar and juice of 1 orange.

title: fruit pizza
directions: First Layer:
Let cookie dough soften and spread in pan.
Cook according to directions.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pick off from bones.
Boil rice. Add chicken, rice and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Add salt to taste.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: Pour water into 12-inch Dutch oven.
Cut up cabbage and sausage into bite-sized pieces and mix together in oven.
Cook 45 minutes
with
coals
on
the
top
and 12 coals on the bottom.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix until blended cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and caramel topping.
Chill, if desired.
Dip apple slices.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients; if using canned mushrooms, do not drain.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 375° for 40 minutes in foil-covered casserole.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes to brown top.

title: sausage-stuffed yams
directions: Cook in covered crock-pot on low setting, 4 to 6 hours.
Cut tops from yams.
Scoop out centers carefully and mash.
Add butter, milk, salt and oregano.
Beat until smooth.
Add sausage. Mix well.
Fill yam shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs just enough to break yolks.
Add to shortening mixture.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Drop.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes, until tender. Cool to touch. Peel and slice. Arrange in a lightly greased 3-quart baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Pour glaze over sweet potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar, juice and rind of lemon.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup cold water and then dissolve again by placing cup in hot water.
After removing first mixture from fire, stir in the dissolved gelatin and cool.
Fold in whipped cream and crushed pineapple.
Beat 6 egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Line a spring mold pan with wax paper.
Place 2 dozen ladyfingers (upright) around the edge, then pour mixture into the mold. Refrigerate for at least 6 or 7 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 5 1/2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: great grandma anna kline's rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and egg yolks.
Mix.
Add milk, cooked rhubarb and cherries.
Fold in beaten egg whites to which some of the sugar can be beaten.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then at 350° until set and golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a baking dish (10 x 14-inches) with hamburger meat.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup on top.
Put mixed vegetables on top of this.
Cover with mushroom soup and place Tater Tots on top. Bake in oven set at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meal in skillet
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in a skillet.
Then brown ground beef in skillet with onions and green pepper.
Season with salt, pepper and adobo season to taste.
When ground beef is brown, add stewed tomatoes and corn.
Let simmer for 15 minutes, then put over rice.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and juices in medium saucepan. Cook and stir until clear (5 to 8 minutes).
Slowly stir in beaten eggs.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickens (3 to 5 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat in cream cheese and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cut slices of bacon in
half;
line sides and bottom of a 1 quart casserole.
Cover
with
half of bread crumbs, tomatoes, green pepper, salt, sugar, butter and corn.
Repeat with layers of remaining ingredients, saving a few bread crumbs for topping.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl, except eggs.
Mix well. Add eggs last and mix well.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: spicy tortilla bites party style
directions: Mix together first two ingredients.
Spread on tortillas. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Roll tortillas as tightly as possible without pushing out the ingredients.
Wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper and refrigerate for a couple of hours or overnight.
Slice and secure with a party toothpick.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Drain fat.
Stir in garlic powder and chili powder.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add tomato juice.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Stir often.
Add beans and heat through.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine 3 cups milk and pudding mix. Beat on low until thick. Fold in whipped topping.

title: apple crisp
directions: You also need an 8 x 8 cake pan.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed.
Add the sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: two step shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened butter with the 1 cup of flour and the confectioners sugar until mixture is crumbly. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Press butter mixture into pan.
Bake 20 minutes until set.
Cool.

title: pizza franks
directions: Cut frankfurters into 1-inch pieces.
Mix tomato sauce and seasonings in a microsafe dish and add frankfurters.
Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken lasagna florentine
directions: Blend soups, Parmesan cheese, sour cream, wine, garlic, chicken, mushrooms and spinach. Make 3 or 4 layers; cover and bake at 350° for at least an hour. Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook cocoa, water and butter in pan until butter is melted.
Put flour, baking soda, vanilla, sugar, eggs and buttermilk in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Ice cake with the following icing while cake is still hot.

title: streusel caramel bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press remainder firmly in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. In saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with condensed milk and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour over crust.
Top with reserved crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Heat apricots in
top
of
double
boiler
over boiling water for 10 minutes.
Put
apricots, coconut and nuts through grinder using a fine
blade.
Knead
ground mixture with lemon rind, lemon and
orange juice.
Add enough confectioners sugar to make a firm mixture.
Form
into
small
balls
and roll in confectioners sugar.
Allow to
dry at room temperature for at least 4 hours. Makes about 1 pound.

title: steak mozzarella
directions: Flour meat and brown in skillet. Remove meat and add remaining ingredients, (except cheese) to skillet. Bring to boil; then pour over meat in 7x11 inch pan. Bake at 300 degrees for 2 to 2 1/2 hrs. Add cheese the last 5 minutes. Serve when cheese melts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer sliced bananas and wafers in a very large bowl.
Mix pudding mix with 3 cups milk until just blended.
Pour in the condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour over the bananas and wafers, using spatula.
Make sure to coat well with the pudding mixture.
Chill well.
(This will make a wash tub full so be sure to use a very large bowl.)

title: sugar free fruit pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk, cream cheese, sweetener, and vanilla with mixer until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and fruit.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixer bowl and beat at medium for 5 minutes.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let sit for 15 minutes before turning out onto plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken and vegetables in a greased casserole.
Cover with soup that has been mixed with broth.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large kettle with water to cover, season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until tender.
Remove chicken from bone. Place chicken broth and 2 cups of the milk into kettle and bring to simmer.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine liquid shortening and 1/3 cup milk.
Add liquids to flour mixture and mix well.
Place dough between waxed paper and roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into kettle of simmering chicken, broth and milk.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste to liquid.
Good dumplings need pepper.

title: "upside down and all around" peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter a 23 cm (9-inch) cake pan; set aside.
Place butter, granulated sugar, whole egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Using electric hand mixer, beat 2 minutes or until mixture becomes thick.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Using wooden spoon, incorporate half of flour into egg mixture in bowl.
Pour in cream and mix well.
Add remaining flour and continue mixing until well incorporated.
Fold in beaten egg whites until no trace of white can be seen; set aside batter.

title: italian chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken parts in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange drained tomato wedges, mushrooms, olive and artichoke hearts on top of chicken.
Combine salad dressing and wine; pour over vegetables and chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done. Cook linguine according to package.
Serve casserole over linguine.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix soda with sour cream and then add to creamed sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Finely add flour and flavoring and pour in tube pan.
Bake for one hour or longer, until done.
I bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then finish at 350°.

title: macaroni and link sausage
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add all ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until sauce thickens.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked macaroni.

title: bread
directions: Combine water and yeast in small bowl.
In 3-quart pan, beat 2 cups of milk.
Slowly add oleo, sugar and salt.
Add the yeast mixture to the milk.
Be sure the milk is now lukewarm.
Stir in 6 cups flour, then 4 more.
Put 2 cups of flour on bread board.
Dump dough on floured board and knead.
Return to bowl and let rise. Punch down.
Make into 3 loaves.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: basic brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and water. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in just about anything you want (1 cup nuts, chocolate chips, coconut, dried fruits, etc.).
The more added makes the cookie more chewy.
Drop in rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: almond chicken pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the chicken, apple, pasta, grapes, celery and onion.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook onions and ground beef until meat loses its red color.
Spoon off any excess fat. Mix meat and soup plus 1/2 can water.
Pour into baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly in the center.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling in bottom of cake pan.
Drain pineapple, spread over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix (do not mix cake mix with water) over cherries and pineapple.
Melt butter and dribble over cake mix.
Spread chopped pecans over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay whole crackers flat to form crust.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut various fruits into bite-size pieces; mix together in large bowl.
Mix honey into yogurt and pour over fruit salad.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter on top of stove for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat and serve.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute meat with onion; when done, add celery and cabbage. Cook until slightly wilted.
In large pot, add all the rest and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Add water to cover.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; bake for 45 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seed for 3 to 5 minutes at 350°. Combine first four ingredients.

title: mrs. johnson's lima beans
directions: Cook lima beans until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine in a saucepan and saute the mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle mushrooms with 6 tablespoons flour, then slowly add the milk.
Stir and cook until sauce thickens and is smooth. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Add the salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mix well.
Add the cooked lima beans and reheat.
Serve piping hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Thaw pie crusts to room temperature.
Mix ingredients in large bowl, except pie crusts.
Carefully put 1 pie crust in the bottom of a 9-inch 2-quart glass baking dish.
Pour ingredients in. Carefully put the 2nd pie crust on top.
Bake in 350° oven until crust is lightly brown.

title: congenial salad
directions: Cream together jello and cream cheese.
Pour 1 cup hot water over mixture; let stand until thickened.
Add crushed, drained pineapple, cherries and chopped walnuts.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Decorate with cherries.

title: garlic and parsley sauce(serves 4)
directions: In a small heavy frying pan, heat the oil until hot, but not smoking.
Add the garlic and saute until golden brown.
Toss the cooked and drained pasta of our choice with the sauce, parsley and seasonings.
Serve immediately.

title: apple butter
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 3 1/2 hours or until thick, stirring every 1/2 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 6 hours. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: edna patton's sweet potato souffle
directions: Sprinkle over potatoes and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.
(May be frozen before baking, then bake longer.)

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Put ingredients in an 11 x 13-inch dish.
Pour water over and bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered with aluminum foil.
You can prepare the day before, but don't add water until you are ready to bake.

title: pink cool whip cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cauliflower meat loaf
directions: Take large cauliflower and remove core, plus 1/4 of the cauliflower.
Stuff with your favorite meat loaf mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350° until done.
Top with favorite cheese topping and bake until cheese melts.
Slice into wedges and serve.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, water and soda; bring to a boil.
Cool completely.
Beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add raisin mixture with flour and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika; roll each piece of chicken in mixture.
Heat oil in baking pan at 400° for 10 minutes.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes; turn and bake another 30 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine water, sugar, and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add peanuts and 6 drops red food coloring.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat; add 1/4 cup oleo and pinch of salt.
Beat until thick.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat, celery, onion and pepper.
Add salt, soy sauce, then add soup and bring to a boil.
Take 1/2 mixture and mix noodles, then take other half and put on top. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add cheese strips just before done, if desired.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Place pretzels and butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; spread over lukewarm pretzel mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese mixture and chill.
Dissolve jello in boiling pineapple juice. Stir in frozen berries.
Allow this to thicken to almost gel point.
Pour over mixture.
Chill about 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Form loaf and put into shallow pan.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water (salted) until tender.
Drain. Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish; place meat on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and cheese; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix over top or buttered bread crumbs.
(Instead of chicken breasts, sliced chicken, turkey or ham may be used.
If using ham, place it on bottom.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken and vegetables
directions: Spread chicken pieces on wax paper.
Brush with lemon juice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; brown quickly on all sides.
Drain oil.
Add sugar, green pepper, onions, broccoli and chicken broth.
Bring to boil; lower heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce; gradually stir in and mix well.
Simmer briefly until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl (use one with lid, preferably Tupperware) mix sugar and cinnamon (easiest to put in bowl, put lid on and shake); set aside.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Open biscuits, one can at a time.
Cut each biscuit in 6 pieces and toss in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
(I usually cut 3 to 4 biscuits at a time, toss in mixture and put in pan.)
As you repeat this process until all biscuits are done, you can add nuts or raisins if desired.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onion together; drain.
Stir in taco mix (do not add water).
Spread in cooking plate, then top with green chilies.
Mix milk, flour and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Last, top with cheese and sliced tomatoes.
Bake an additional 8 minutes.

title: squash turnovers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil in frying pan.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn over, fry on both sides. Turnovers may be cooled and frozen, placing wax paper between each.
Thaw and reheat.

title: dad's favorite corned beef hash
directions: Mix corned beef hash with mustard.
Place half of mixture in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place layer of onion, tomato, then cheese over hash.
Repeat layers again.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: canned green beans
directions: Wash and break beans.
Mix all the ingredients and cook 30 minutes in open kettle.
Put in jars; seal and store.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add peanut butter and blend well. Add powdered sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla; mix well.
Pour carefully into graham cracker crusts and spread around.
Replace covers and put into refrigerator overnight or quick method, put into freezer for 1 hour.

title: snow covered mix
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter.
Combine cereal, pretzels, raisins and peanuts; coat with the melted mixture, then sift through powdered sugar.
(Makes a lot; good for the holidays.)

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all in bowl. Press in 9 x 13 pan. Spread topping over it and refrigerate until cold.

title: spaghetti squash dinner(weight watchers)
directions: Microwave spaghetti squash on High for 10 minutes or until done.
When soft, cut in half, seed and empty sides into bowl. Brown turkey with onion and mushrooms.
Add squash, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Heat.
Place in squash shells.
Top with cheese. Bake until cheese melts.
Serves 2; 4 protein and 5 vegetables.

title: sour cream-lemon pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is consistency of fine crumbs.
Sprinkle water over flour mixture and blend well.
Press into firm ball.
Flatten slightly and roll out to 12-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Fit loosely into one 9-inch pie pan and trim 1/2-inch beyond rim of pan.
Fold under and flute edge.
Prick thoroughly.
Bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not prick shell if shell and filling are to be baked together.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Stir in the egg yolks, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Add remaining margarine and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil and boils for 1 minute.
Pour into a bowl and cover surface with waxed paper or plastic film.
Chill, then fold in sour cream.
Turn into the baked pastry shell and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Stir constantly while cooking. Cook until they reach the firm ball stage on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and food coloring.
Beat with a wooden spoon until it loses its glossy appearance.
Immediately spoon onto wax paper.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together.
Beat in vanilla flavoring and eggs.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Put 3 M&M's on cookies before baking.
Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: Cut vegetables bias cut.
Heat oil in Dutch oven; add beef, cut in 1-inch cubes.
Brown 20 minutes.
Add onion and garlic; cook 10 minutes.
Add liquid ingredients.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: old-fashioned apple pan
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan, then add water, vinegar and lemon juice. Stir until smooth. Bring rapidly to a boil and cook 2 to 3 minutes stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from the heat.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of square cake pan.
Dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Spread cake mix on top of cherries. Pour butter, melted, over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serve hot or cold with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil in nonstick pan.
Remove when onions and celery are soft.
Cut up chicken breast in cubes and cook until no longer pink.
Drain chicken.
Add celery, onions, olives, tomatoes and 1 jar salsa.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Take 2 tablespoons of mixture and place in center of taco shell.
Fold lengthwise, then fold ends.
Place fold side down in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Repeat.
Pour remaining jar of salsa over tacos.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: health salad
directions: Toss fruit, vegetables and cheese together in a large bowl. Mix white wine and mayonnaise; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill. Serves 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Add beaten eggs to milk gradually, then add sugar, salt. Pour into unbaked 9 inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake 20 minutes at 400°, then lower heat to 350° and bake until done. Test by inserting toothpick in center.
When toothpick comes out clean pie is done.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Drain macaroni.
In a large bowl, mix macaroni, mixed vegetables, tomato (chopped), cucumber (chopped), 1 cup mayo and meat.
Mix together well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: blender dough
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle the yeast over 3 cups warm water.
Let sit.
In blender, put the next 5 ingredients; mix and add to yeast and water.
Add the flour to the liquid.
Knead about 10 minutes, then let rise.
Punch down.
Make bread, rolls or cinnamon rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves of bread or 2 large pans of rolls.

title: mom's zucchini relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse salt off thoroughly.
Add both peppers.
In a pan, heat spices, sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Add vegetables and simmer 30 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package instructions. Cool. Poke holes on top and pour Kahlua over the entire surface. Prepare mousse with Cool Whip. Sprinkle crushed Heath bars over the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: toasted seasoned pecans
directions: Place pecans in a 1 1/2-quart microproof dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cut oleo or butter in 8 pieces.
Space evenly on top of pecans.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: easy dessert salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Simmer for 2 hours and thicken with flour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Mix all ingredients, except juice.
Make into patties and cook.
When cooked, return all patties to skillet and cover with tomato juice.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer, until juice cooks down and becomes thick.

title: rocky road
directions: Grease with margarine a 8-inch pan.
Put marshmallows in pan. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Dribble peanut butter and chocolate mixture over marshmallows.
Put candy into refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle sides with half of the graham cracker crumbs.
Completely dissolve jello in boiling water in small bowl.
Pour into blender container; add cheeses.
Blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes, or until mixture is completely smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pie pan.
Smooth top.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs around outside edge, leaving center plain.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Beat egg and milk together. In bowl, mix together all dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Make a well and pour in egg/milk mixture. Stir until the dough follows the fork. Knead on floured board gently (make the dough easier to handle, not sticky, but don't add too much flour). Pat the dough to about 3/4-inch thick and cut. The less you handle the dough, the fluffier the biscuit. Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pink champagne
directions: Mix together and enjoy.

title: flavory pot roast or chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Wipe meat off with paper towel. Place in shallow	baking	pan.
Sprinkle	with onion soup mix, then add undiluted mushroom soup.
Cover.
Bake 2 1/2 hours or until done. Use drippings for gravy.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna italian
directions: Cook onion until tender but not brown.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Heat and stir.
Break tuna in chunks; add with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with minced parsley and ripe olives.
Pass lemon wedges.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together devil's food cake mix, 3 eggs and butter/margarine.
Pat in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Beat together cream cheese, 2 eggs, box confectioners sugar and vanilla until blended.
Put on top of pecans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Put one at a time layered in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: bread pudding
directions: Fill a 3 or 4-quart bowl with stale bread.
Put sugar on top. Set aside.
Beat eggs and add extract and warm milk with butter until melted.
Pour milk on top of bread, then add egg and extract mixture.
Beat until well blended.
If desired, add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in angel food cake pan.
May be sliced like a cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Combine chicken and both soups in a bowl; pour into baking pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granma's eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Set egg whites aside.
Beat egg yolks; add brandy, one tablespoon at a time while continuously beating (should look like thin custard when done).
Stir in half and half, milk and sugar.
Stir in rum.
Whip cream until stiff and fold in mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Refrigerate.
Shake before serving.
Sprinkle nutmeg on before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain. Save 3 Tbsp. drippings in saucepan. Add onion and celery to drippings in pan; cook and stir until onion is tender. Remove from heat; blend in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil and stir 1 minutes. Stir in corn, potatoes, salt and pepper; heat through. Stir in bacon. Sprinkle each serving with parsley and paprika. Serves 6.

title: microwave turkey enchiladas
directions: Prepare pan, sauce and turkey mixture as directed.
Place tortillas between layers of paper towels on full power 45 to 60 seconds or until pliable.
Assemble tortillas with filling in pan. Micro-cook covered on High for 3 minutes.
Top with remaining sauce and shredded cheese.
Micro-cook uncovered on High for 1 minute more or until sauce is hot.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 servings.

title: easy tex-mex dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayonnnaise, and taco seasoning in a small bowl, set aside.
On a serving plate or pan, layer bean dip, quacamole, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, onions, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips or fritoes.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (peeled and chopped).
Drain well.
Beat in cream cheese, sour cream, garlic salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mi-maw's easy cookies
directions: *Two eggs if you
want	it where you can drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon.

title: tomato soup
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the butter in large pot and add olive oil.
Add the onions, thyme, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is wilted.
Add the tomatoes and tomato paste and stir to blend.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place flour in small bowl and add 5 tablespoons chicken broth, stirring to blend.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Add remaining broth and simmer 30 minutes. Put soup through blender.
Return to heat and add sugar and cream. Simmer 5 minutes.
Swirl in remaining butter and top with croutons.

title: healthy adapted eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant; dip in egg substitute and coat with breadcrumbs.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick coating and bake eggplant slices in a 350° oven until soft.
Top with your favorite sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: cathy's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add 1/2 stick butter or oleo and cubed cheese.
Stir until cheese starts to melt.
Mix crushed crackers with 1/2 stick oleo, which has been melted.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour broccoli-cheese mixture into casserole dish.
Top with buttered cracker mixture.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Melt butter; thaw potatoes enough to mix well.
Combine all other ingredients, except cheese, with potatoes and butter. Pour into greased 9X13 pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 for 45-60 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat and add eggs; mix.
Add vanilla, sugar and dates; allow to melt.
Mix together over low heat and cut up dates with spatula while stirring constantly.
Simmer 5 minutes (creamy mixture).
Remove from heat. Add pecans and Rice Krispies; mix thoroughly.
Cool slightly. Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: generon(french apple cobbler)
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch deep pie dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and brandy.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Beat together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat for 2 minutes. Fold in the flour and baking powder.
Pour this mixture over the apples and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream or sweetened whipped cream.
Serves 4. Can easily be doubled.

title: spinach khoresh
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil in a 4-quart saucepan on medium-high heat.
Add meat and stir, cooking until meat is no longer red.
Add turmeric, salt and mint, mixing well.
Add water; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add all the greens and the potatoes, mixing well to thaw.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until the meat is tender.
Add the lemon juice and, if too thick, add some water.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Gradually add to the beaten egg whites, beating all the while.
Add vanilla and beat until candy loses its gloss and stands in peaks.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Top with cherries or nuts, if desired.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: wild duck
directions: Place prepared duck in roaster with about 1-inch of water in pan.
Salt and pepper duck; add one small onion.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours at 375°, basting often.
Drain off fat and add enough cornstarch to drippings to make gravy to the consistency to which you like it.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crumbs, egg, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into 20 balls and brown in olive oil.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour soup mixture over meatballs and gently simmer for 1/2 hour.
More water may be added to have a thinner sauce.

title: jewish crumb coffee cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.
Beat butter to cream; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add salt and eggs.
Beat at high speed on electric mixer.
Sift flour with baking soda and add to beaten mixture alternately with sour cream on low speed.

title: bridal punch
directions: Have your ginger ale and Sprite well chilled. When ready to use, mix them with lemon juice and pineapple juice. Add sherbet.

title: "seven layer salad"
directions: Tear the lettuce up in small pieces in the bottom of the bowl. Layer with chopped onion.
Next layer is chopped celery, then drain the peas and spread evenly over the other ingredients. Spread the mayo over the ingredients you have so far.
Sprinkle a dash of sugar over the mayo.
Spread the bacon bits evenly over mayo.
Sprinkle the cheese evenly also.
A meal in itself!

title: homemade waffles
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron until done.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 3 or 4 hours before eating.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water, then add the remaining ingredients.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spanish beans
directions: Put all in pot; cook as you would dry beans.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and 1/2 stick of butter.
Mix together all ingredients, except Cheez Whiz.
Pour into glass baking dish.
On top of this, pour Cheez Whiz that has been melted per directions on jar.
Cook at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
If cheese is getting too brown, may want to cover with foil and continue cooking.

title: baked eggplant or zucchini
directions: Wash, dry and slice eggplant or zucchini into 1/4-inch slices. Dip into beaten egg; dip into flour.
Lay vegetables flat on sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: lisa's favorite peach pie
directions: Cook marshmallows and milk in double boiler; cool.
Add whipped cream.
Mix with marshmallow mix.
Add peaches; pour into cooled pie shell.

title: orange cream cheese glaze
directions: Mix cream cheese, extract, Equal and enough milk to make medium glaze consistency.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: You can substitute an 8-inch pan for this cheesecake recipe, if desired.
The large cheesecake will require only 45 to 50 minutes baking time.
